(1, 'Namasthe', 'Namasthe is a customary, non-contact form of Hindu greeting. Namaste is usually spoken with a slight bow and hands pressed together, palms touching and fingers pointing upwards. Namaste is used as a form of greeting, acknowledging, and welcoming a relative, guest, or stranger. In some contexts, it can be used to express gratitude for assistance offered or given and to thank people for their generosity. ', 'The gesture of joining both hands has more than a symbolic meaning. It is said to provide a connection between the right and left hemispheres of the brain thus representing unification.', 'people2', 'girl', 'all', 'greeting, custom, symbolic, namasthe', 'Slide1.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhita', NULL),
(2, 'Salwar Kameez', 'The salwar kameez is a sleek, contemporary dress design originating from the Indian state of Punjab. The \'kameez\' is a knee length tunic with lots of intricate adornments. The \'salwar\' are loose pajama-like trousers. The salwar kameez is worn both as an everyday outfit, as well as formal wear. It is often accompanied by a shawl, known as the \"dupatta\".', 'In some regions of Asia, this dress is worn by both men and women.', 'Punjab, Casual Occasion', 'girl', 'Punjab', 'woman, regional, salwar, kameez, punjab', 'Slide2.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(3, 'Gujarathi Saree', 'Gujarathi saree, also known as Surat saree, is a very interesting variation of the traditional saree. In this dress, the pallu (or drape) is worn hanging forward as opposed to hanging back over one shoulder. These sarees are usually found in the Bandhej print, which is uniquely found in Gujarat. These sarees are generally only worn on special occasions, such as weddings and festivals, but also can be found in plain colors for everyday life.', 'Any sari can be draped in the Gujarathi style. This is most apparent during the Garba dances.', 'regional, special occasion ', 'girl', 'Gujarath', 'saree, surat, gujarath, pallu, bandhej, women, dance', 'Slide3.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(4, 'Saree', 'Saree is a cultural icon worn by women in India. It is a continuous weave of fabric, 4-12 meters or 15-30 feet long draped around a woman in different ways. This fabric is traditionally made from natural fibers like Cotton & silk. Man made fibers like polyester, chiffon are also used. It is worn with an upper garment called \'choli or saree blouse\'. And a lower underlayer called petticoat which gives the Saree some form. \r\n', 'There are more than 100 ways of wearing a saree!', 'Regional', 'girl', 'All', 'Saree, Sari', 'Slide4.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(5, 'Kerala Kasavu', 'The Kasavu style saree is a traditional dress worn by the people of Kerala. During historical times, patterned dresses were seen as a \"crime\", so a minimalistic approach was used. These sarees are always white in color, and cotton in fabric, with a colored border. If the border is gold, it is considered to be an expensive sari and is generally worn at weddings. If it is any other color, then it is worn every day.', 'The wider the colored border, the more luxurious it is considered to be!', 'regional', 'girl', 'Kerala', 'white, saree, gold, border', 'Slide5.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(6, 'Maharashtra Nauvari ', 'The Nauvari saree is traditionally worn by the women in Maharashtra. Nauvari means 9 yards, so each saree is exactly 9 yards! The style of it has evolved over many years, to the modern way of a trouser-like appearance where the saree is tucked in the back.', 'Historically, Marathi women assisted male warriors during the times of war. Hence, in order to have physical movement during the wars, they invented the style of drape.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Maharashtra', 'nauvari, dresses, regional', 'Slide6.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(7, 'Garad Saree', 'Garad Silk is a popular style of saree that comes from West Bengal. The word \'garad\' means white and these sarees are distinguished by its red border and small designs around it.', 'The color white is a symbol of purity and so Bengali women tend to wear this dress on special and religious occasions.', 'Religious, Festivals, Special Occasions', 'girl', 'West Bengal', 'saree, red, garad', 'Slide7.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(8, 'Madisar Kattu', 'The Madisar Kattu is a saree style from the state of Tamil Nadu. This dress uses several different materials woven together to create the final look. It consists of a full-length blouse and shawl. This style of wearing saree is also called Pavada, or half saree. ', 'Another saree from this region of India is called the Kanchipuram Saree, which is worn on more special occasions. ', 'Regional', 'girl', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Saree, Shawl, Blouse, Pavada', 'Slide8.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(9, 'Rajasthani Dress', 'The Rajasthani dress is worn with a lehenga and blouse. The dupatta is wrapped elegantly all around the body and over the head. These dresses come in very intricate designs, and the base colors are often tie-dye. In Rajasthan, wearing a considerable amount of jewelry during every day normal life is not abnormal. So this dress is often worn with lots of jewelry, bangles, and anklets. ', 'Rajasthani culture is very colorful, and in keeping with this, Rajasthani dresses are also very colorful and festive.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Rajasthan', ' Lehenga, blouse, dupatta, tie-dye, jewelry, anklets, bangles', 'Slide9.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Nikhitha', NULL),
(10, 'Lambadi Dress', 'The Lambadi dress, is worn by the tribal women from Rajasthan. There is a lehenga and blouse, and the dupatta is tucked into the lehenga, and begins to wrap like a saree, but only goes around about halfway and then is wrapped around the head. The designs of this dress consist of many small mirrors, and lots of colors. Like other dresses from Rajasthan, it is worn with lots of jewelry. ', 'The Lambadi or Banjara people originated from the deserts of Rajasthan, but have spread their tribes across India to the south.', 'regional, tribal', 'girl', 'originating from Rajasthan, has spread to southern India', 'Lambadi, banjara, tribal, lehenga, blouse, dupatta, mirrors, jewelry', 'Slide10.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(11, 'Coorgi Saree', 'The Coorgi saree is a style from Karnataka. The pallu is draped over the shoulder from the back instead from the front and saree pleats pushed backwards. This saree is also known as Kodagu Style Saree or Kodava Attire. Traditionally, this saree is red, but it can be worn with any color cloth.', 'The women also wear a headpiece that is called Vastra', 'regional', 'girl', 'Karnataka', 'coorgi, karnataka, backwards, pallu, golden, plain', 'Slide11.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(12, 'Kashmiri Pheran ', 'The traditional dress from Kashmir is called Pheran, which is a long cloak worn across the body. The taranga is the headdress accompanied with this dress. Pants to go with this are generally salwar. Women in Kashmir are expected to wear this for everyday life, and fancier designs for special occasions and weddings', 'The Pheran is worn by both men and women. It sometimes consists of two gowns worn over each other.', 'Regional', 'girl', 'Kashmir', 'Pheran, Taranga, Salwar', 'Slide12.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(13, 'Bihu Dress', 'Bihu is a festival and traditional folk dance that celebrates the harvest season in Assam. The women performers of Bihu wear a traditional lower bogy garment known as Mekhala while a chaddar is used to cover the upper portion of the body. Women also wear jewelry and put flowers in their plaits to celebrate the spirit of spring. ', 'The Bihu  dance is  among the finest highlights of the festival.  It is a group performance where the  women dance in  linear and circular patterns and enter after the men.', 'festival, dance, regional', 'girl', 'Assam', 'traditional, folk, harvest, spring', 'Slide13.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(14, 'Lehenga Choli', 'The Lehenga Choli is a three-piece attire. The Lehenga is a long skirt which is usually embellished or embroidered and is worn with a fitted blouse. A  Ghagra Choli is very similar to the lehenga choli. It consists of a long flowing skirt made of cotton, but more loose fitting than the lehenga skirt. Though it can be simple with just a plain color, in some states the cotton is woven into very intricate designs. The choli is the blouse, usually cut a bit short above the waist. This is usually worn with the dupatta/chuni, across the neck. The ghagra choli is a bit more traditional in Rajasthan, Gujarat, Haryana, and Punjab.', 'Lehenga Cholis became popular in the 10th century when fine craftsmanship was  developed after the arrival of Mughals in India.', 'festival', 'girl', 'Northern India', 'girls, women, festival, lehenga', 'Slide14.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria ', NULL),
(15, 'Goa Koli Dress', 'Fisherwomen from Goa wear this style of saree so the cloth will not get wet easily. The drape is tied at the waist and is wrapped around both legs making a sort of pants with the cloth. This dress has also inspired modern fashion and many women wear the modern version of this half-dhoti under kurtis (longer shirts).', 'This is also known as the \"Half Dhoti\" look.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Goa', 'women, girls, fishermen, occupational', 'Slide15.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(16, 'Kurta Dupatta', 'Kurta is a simple knee-length tunic dress that is worn across India. It can be paired with jeans, leggings, churidar, or salwar. Often this dress is worn with the dupatta (chunni), which is a shawl-like scarf that can be worn in several styles. The kurta dupatta combination comes in very simple styles and also with very intricate patterns.', 'The kurta style became popular in India during the 1900s, but it is also worn in the U.S., U.K., Italy, France, and the Middle East. ', 'All', 'girl', 'All', 'Dupatta,  Jeans, Leggings, Churidar, Salwar, Chunni, Scarf, Shawl', 'Slide16.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(17, 'gochi kaTTu', 'This drape is worn by the shepherd and agriculture communities of Telangana. Traditionally, it is a single piece of unstitched fabric with various densities. Today, it includes textiles woven by mill or by hand.', 'The various densities of the fabric allows it to be more easily draped.', 'Regional', 'girl', 'Telangana, Andhra Pradesh', 'farmer, agriculture, saree, textiles', 'Slide17.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(18, 'Milk Maid', 'Milkmaids are women who milk cows. They also generally prepare products made out of the milk, such as churning butter or making buttermilk. Milkmaids work all over India.', 'Indian milkmaids typically carry urns on their heads because they can hold 3-4 urns at once. Some women even balance urns on their heads completely.  ', 'women, India, people', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'milk, maid, women', 'Slide18.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(19, 'Puanchei', 'The Puanchei is the traditional dress of Mizoram. It is two pieces (full sleeves top and skirt) sown together with intricate designs. The skirt is not flowy like the lehenga/ghagra, but rather straight and stiff made from cotton. The base color is generally white with black, green, and red horizontal and vertical stripes across. The headpiece is like a woven crown with \'flowers\' coming up that have a green stem and red flower.', 'The Puanchei is worn on nearly all occasions in Mizoram, from religious occasions to weddings!', 'regional, religious, festivals, weddings', 'girl', 'Mizoram', 'puanchei, mizoram, headpiece, flowers', 'Slide19.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(20, 'Khasi Dress', 'Women who belong to the Khasi tribe of Meghalaya wear a Jainsen and blouse. The Jainsen wrap covers the body from the waist to ankles. On top, a cotton shawl called tap-moh khlieh is worn, and it looks similar to an apron. Ornaments of pure gold and silver are usually worn along with the beautiful outfit. Senior women of the tribe also wear Jainkup, which is made from woolen cloth. On special occasions, a fancier version of this dress can be worn.', 'The Khasi dress, along with the Jaintia and Garo outfits make up the three major tribes of Meghalaya.', 'Regional, Occasion', 'girl', 'Meghalaya', 'Jainsen, Khasi, Tap-Moh Khlieh, Jainkup', 'Slide20.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(21, 'Angami Dress', 'The Angami Dress style is from Nagaland. There is a plain cloth skirt (white color). It has thick black marginal bands of a variety of breadth. The ladies also wear Mechala, that wrap around the skirt with an accompanying shawl.', 'Different tribes in Nagaland have their own festivals. On average, there is one major festival lined up for all the months in the year!', 'regional, tribal', 'girl', 'Nagaland', 'angami, nagaland, skirt, mechala, shawl', 'Slide21.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
