(26, 'Yamini Krishnamurty', 'Yamini Krishnamurty was born on 20th December, 1940 in Chittoor, Andhra Pradesh. She began her training at the Kalakshetra, a leading school for dance. Yamini Krishnamurthy currently teaches dance to children at her dance institute, Yamini School of Dance in New Delhi. Krishnamurthy has been felicitated by the Padma Shree (1968), Padma Bhushan (2001), and the Padma Vibhushan (2016) for her contribution to Indian dance. She was also awarded the Natya Shastra award by Shambhavi School of Dance in 2014.', 'The title of Asthana Narthaki (“Resident Dancer”) was bestowed upon her by the Tirumala Tirupathi Devasthanam temple (in Tirupathi, AP).', 'dance, classical', 'girl', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'dance, classical', 'Slide26.PNG', 'writeup_done', '', 'book1'),
(27, 'Rukmini Devi Arundale', 'Rukmini Devi Arundale was born in Madurai, Tamil Nadu. As a young adult, Rukmini  became involved in the Theosophical Society of India, became a theosophist herself, and married Dr. George Arundale. At the behest of the famous Russian ballerina Anna Pavlova,  Rukmini dedicated herself to reviving various Indian dance and art forms. She established the Kalakshetra foundation and went on to become a great Bharatanatyam dancer. Rukmini is well known to have declined the Presidency of India to pursue her career in dance. She also became the first female Indian to have been nominated to the Rajya Sabha.\r\n', 'She was born on a unique leap year day - 29th February 1904.', 'dance, classical', 'girl', 'Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh', 'dance, classical ', 'Slide27.PNG', 'writeup_done', '', 'book1'),
(28, 'Sanjukta Panigrahi', 'Sanjukta Panigrahi started learning Odissi under Guru Kelucharan Mohapatra at the age of four. During one of her performances a the age of six she refused to get down from the stage and continued dancing enthusiastically. She later started training under the able guidance of Rukmini Devi Arundale. She is reputed for have brought back the dying dance of Odissi. She died in 1997 at the age of 54. \r\n', 'Sanjukta Panigrahi was the first Odia woman to have ensured the revival of the great dance form, Odissi.', 'Dances', 'girl', 'Orissa', 'Classical, Odissi', 'Slide28.PNG', 'proposed', '', 'book1'),
(29, 'Sitara Devi', 'Sitara Devi was born in Calcutta on November 8, 1920. She started learning dance under her father who had established a dancing school. When she was ten years of age, she was conferred with the title of Nritya Samragni by Rabindranath Tagore. She later performed in many movies such as Roti, Watan, Mother India, etc. Sitara Devi was also accomplished in many other dance forms such as Russian Balet, Bharatanatyam, and many other folk dances. She died on 25 Novemeber, 2014 after a prolonged illness.\r\n', 'She also taught many famous Bollywood actresses such as Rekha, Madhubala and Kajol.', 'regional, dances', 'girl', 'North India', 'dances, dresses, kathak', 'Slide29.PNG', 'proposed', '', 'book1'),
(30, 'Mohiniyattam', 'Kalamandalam Kalyanikutty Amma was an extremely prominent Mohiniyattam dancer. She was one of the early students of Kerala Kalamandalam and has mastered the art of Mohiniyattam. She taught many students and among them Mrinalini Sarabhai, Kala Vijayan, and Deepti Omcherry Bhalla went on to achieve great things. She was awarded with the Kerala Sangeetha nataka Akademi Award and the Kendraa Sangeet natak Akademi Award. In 2019, her grand daughter Smita Rajan, who is a dancer herself produced a movie, \'Mother of Mohiniyattam\', on Kalamandalam Kalyanikutty Amma.  \r\n', 'She married Kathakali artist, Kalamandalam Krishnan Nair. \r\n', 'dance, classical', 'girl', 'Kerala', 'dance, classical, girls, women', 'Slide30.PNG', 'proposed', '', 'book1'),
(31, 'Kathakali', 'Kathakali is a classical dance form of Kerala. The costumes in this art form are generally very large and heavy. There are different costumes for different characters. The main dancers don the costume with different colored jackets along with multi-colored scarves and pleated skirts.', 'Kathakali is traditionally a male art form but modern day women are striving to learn and become a part of the art form as well.', 'dance, regional', 'girl', 'Kerala', 'dance, classical, colorful, men', 'Slide31.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(32, 'Phanek Innaphi', 'This is the traditional dress from Manipur. It is worn during the Manipuri form of classical dance. There is a shawl/wrap around for the upper body called Innaphi. The skirt-long sarong is called the Phanek. For the most traditional look, a feather-decked headpiece is also worn. The Phanek generally has horizontal like patterns and the Innaphi has floral designs around it.', 'Originally, the Innaphi of this dress was made out of bark from creepers known as Uriphi!', 'Regional', 'girl', 'Manipur', 'Phanek, Innaphi, Sarong, Skirt, Feathers, Headpiece, Shawl', 'Slide32.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(33, 'Sattriya', 'Sattriya is an Indian Classical Dance from Assam. The costumes are usually made with Pat - a silk produced in Assam. It is derived from the mulberry plant and woven into intricate motifs. The male costume consists of a Dhoti, Chadar, and Paguri (turban) while the female costume consists of a Ghuri, Chadar, and Kanchi (waist cloth). Performers also wear traditional Assamese jewelry when performing.', 'One-act plays of Sattriya are called Ankiya Nat, which combine aesthetics and religion through a ballad, dance, and drama. ', 'regional, dance', 'girl', 'Assam', 'dance, classical, plays, drama', 'Slide33.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Nikhitha', NULL),
(34, 'Langa Jacket', 'The lehenga is a long flowing skirt that is worn differently in separate regions of India. This can be worn on religious events, and at weddings. It comes in simple designs and very intricate gemmed styles. It is generally worn with a blouse on top, but that can be replaced with a T-shirt. Usually a dupatta/chunni is worn with it. ', 'Each state of India has their own style of lehenga!', 'religious, festivals, weddings, any occasion', 'girl', 'all', 'lehenga, skirt, blouse, t-shirt', 'Slide34.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(35, 'Pattu Pavadai', 'Pattu Pavadai is a style of lehenga worn by girls that distinguishes them as unmarried (worn before marriage). Usually consisting of the lehenga (floor-length skirt) and blouse (generally waist length). This version of lehenga is not usually worn with dupatta/chunni.', 'This dress is also called Langa Voni.', 'southern India, before marriage', 'girl', 'South India', 'pattu pavadai, lehenga, blouse, southern India, girls, teens', 'Slide35.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(36, 'Bhangra Dance (Female)', 'Bhangra refers to several forms of folk dance and music originating in Punjab. Bhangra dances are usually performed in during the harvest season. Bhangra dresses have loose trousers called salwar, and a knee-length or shorter tunic, called kameez. (Also known as salwar kameez.) A long dupatta is sometimes worn, draped around the head or in a different manner. In addition, a vest might be worn on top of the kameez. ', 'The largest Bhangra performance was performed by over 21,000 participants in Ludhiana India.', 'Regional, Seasonal, Dance', 'girl', 'Punjab', 'Harvest, Colorful, Salwar, Kameez', 'Slide36.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana ', NULL),
(37, 'Dandiya Dress', 'Dandiya is a religious folk dance from the Indian State of Gujarat. It is performed/played during the Hindu Navaratri festival. For this dance, you use two sticks and tap them together to match with the beat of the music. Women and Gujarat dress in very traditional lehengas with lots of jewelry, bangles, and anklets for this dance.  ', 'This dance is also performed in some regions of Rajasthan!', 'regional, religious, festivals', 'girl', 'Gujarat, Rajasthan', 'dandiya, dance, jewelry, bangles, anklets, navaratri', 'Slide37.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(38, 'Vana Kanya', 'Vana Kanya refers to the lady in the forest. It is a part of common folk lore and history', '', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide38.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria\nSiva Jasthi', NULL),
(39, 'Rani Rudrama Devi', 'Rani Rudrama Devi was the reigning monarch of the Kakatiya dynasty (located in present day Telangana and Andhra Pradesh). In order to be one of the few female monarchs, she promoted a male image. Unlike her predecessors, she recruited warriors who were not from aristocratic families as a token of appreciation of their support. ', 'She was among the few and the most successful female rulers of South Asian history. ', 'people', 'girl', 'NA', 'queen, woman', 'Slide39.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', 'book1'),
(40, 'Maharashtra Turban (Female)', 'The Maharashtra Turban, also known as Marathi Pheta, is a style of wearing the turban only found in the state of Maharashtra. The Pheta is basically a long cotton cloth (11-20 feet) that is wrapped around the head. It is made of cotton, and some traditional colors for it include saffron and white.', 'This turban is worn by men, women, girls, and boys across the state of Maharashtra!', 'Regional', 'girl', 'Maharashtra', 'Turban, Marathi, Pheta', 'Slide40.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(41, 'Chattisgarh Tribal Dress', 'The women of Chhattisgarh are famous for wearing \"Ludga\" (saree) and \"Polkha\" (blouse) along with attractive ornaments and jewels which is an integral part of their culture and heritage. The sarees are made with bright and vibrant colors and often have various textiles sewn on them. ', 'Chhattisgarh is well known for its tribal weaving since ancient times, a skill set that had been adopted from the different tribal cultures.', 'regional, tribal', 'girl', 'Chattisgarh', 'saree, colorful, textiles', 'Slide41.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(42, 'Shakuntala', ' Shakuntala is a popular character from the Mahabharata. Her husband was King Dushyanta and her son King Bharatha. One famous story about her involves the curse of the sage Durvasa as Shakuntala failed to greet him properly. But the curse was eventually lifted and Shakuntala, Bharat, and Dushyanta lived happily ever after. There are many other interesting stories about her.', 'She was the daughter of the great sage Vishwamitra and Menaka', 'women, regional', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'stories, women', 'Slide42.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(43, 'Anarkali', 'The Anarkali is a type of salwar kameez. It is a very elegant and sophisticated type of dress. There are many different fabrics, necklines, and patterns that make up the Anarkali. It is form-fitting at the top and flows into a looser fitted skirt. Anarkali suits owe their name to the fictional Anarkali, a courtesan in the court of Mughal emperor Akbar.', 'There are certain very detailed Anarkalis that are made for the bride at weddings!', 'regional, dresses', 'girl', 'All across India, Pakistan, certain parts of the Middle East', 'women, India, dresses', 'Slide43.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Smriti', NULL),
(44, 'Palazzo Pants', 'Palazzo is an Italian word literally meaning a large, splendid palace or building. Palazzo pants are trousers with very wide legs to move around freely .', 'The first known use of palazzo pants was in 1956.', 'Occasional, Fancy Dress', 'girl', 'All', 'Pants, Palazzo', 'Slide44.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(45, 'Namboothiri  Saree', 'The Namboothiri  Saree Drape from Kerala includes two pieces of cloth that are either tucked in to the blouse or shoulder. This saree is generally worn at folk dances during Onam, a harvest festival.', 'The Namboothiri is the oldest form of saree in India.', 'regional, festival', 'girl', 'Kerala', 'harvest, saree, traditional, Onam', 'Slide45.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(46, 'Lehenga Choli', 'Lehenga Choli is a long and flowing skirt, made out of several different materials, and it is adorned with all sorts of gems and patterns. The choli (top) is usually designed to match the skirt and the colors of it accent the skirt. It is generally worn with a long dupatta that can be worn in several different styles, but sometimes the dupatta is left out.This dress is very similar to the Ghagra Choli, but it is more formal, heavy, and for special occasion, whereas the ghagra choli skirt is made out of cotton and for everyday life. Outfits such as the lehenga choli are often worn for weddings and religious occasions.', 'There are 10 different types of lehenga skirt styles!', 'religious, festivals, special occasion', 'girl', 'ALL', 'lehenga, skirt, blouse, top, choli, dupatta, ', 'Slide46.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(47, 'Tricolor Saree', 'Most Tricolor Sarees have the following colors: Saffron(orange), green, and white. There are tricolor sarees in other colors, however, they are uncommon. Most women choose to wear this Saree for Independence day/ republic day as the 3 colors are of the Indian Flag.', 'This saree is only worn on special occasions.', 'festivals, dresses', 'girl', 'NA', 'saree, occasional, patriotism', 'Slide47.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(48, 'Bharat Mata', 'Bharat Mata is a painting by artist Abanindranath Tagore. It is of a saffron clothed woman, dressed like a sadhvi. Sadhvi is also known as a woman who is very virtuous, honest, and righteous. In this painting she has four hands. Each is holding one of the following: a book, sheaves of paddy, a piece of white cloth, and a garland. This was painted in 1905, during the larger Indian independence movement.', 'The painter, Abanindranath Tagore, was the nephew of Rabindranath Tagore, a very renowned poet and musical artist. ', 'Other', 'girl', 'All', 'Tagore,  Independence, patriotism', 'Slide48.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(49, 'Lehenga Suit', 'A Lehenga is a long skirt that can be worn in many different outfits. A Lehenga suit is a popular variant of a Lehenga. This consists of a straight-cut kurta which falls below the knee and a Lehenga that can be worn below. There are usually no pants in this outfit as the Lehenga usually falls all the way till your ankle or below. Lehenga suits can be made from several different types of materials. Brocade is often used for a regal Lehenga style suit.', 'Lehengas have been popular since the Mughal era when they were created and worn by women. ', 'Occassional', 'girl', 'All', 'skirt, kurta, lehenga, festive', 'Slide49.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(50, 'Mother Teresa', ' Agnes Gonxhe Bojaxhiu, known to the world as \'Mother Teresa\' was an Albanian-Indian famous nun, who founded the Missionaries of Charity. She lived in India most of her life helping the poor and weak. She became a nun at a very young age. She was admired all over the world for her charitable work, including feeding the hungry, and looking after the sick.\r\n', 'Mother Teresa won the Nobel Peace Prize for her charitable contributions to society.', 'dresses, regional, religious, author', 'girl', 'Kolkata', 'Nun', 'Slide50.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', 'book1'),
(51, 'Half Skirt and Gown', 'The High-Low skirt is originally from the Victorian era. This dress, however, has made a come back in recent times. The front of the skirt is shorter than the back of the skirt which looks similar to a gown. This skirt can be worn with many types of tops, but is generally worn with a crop top.', 'This style is also known as \"asymmetrical\", \"waterfall\", or \"mullet skirt\"', 'dresses', 'girl', 'NA', 'skirt, high-low', 'Slide51.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(52, 'Mithali Raj', 'Mithali Raj is an Indian cricketer and was previously the captain of India\'s women\'s national cricket team. She was born in Rajasthan and started taking cricket coaching at the age of ten with her elder brother. She is considered as a role model for many. At the 2013 Women\'s World Cup, she was the top ranked cricketer in the ODI series (One day International). Mithali has set many records, to name a few: only female cricketer to surpass 7,000 runs in Women\'s ODI, first female cricketer to reach 2,000 runs int the 20-20 format (20 overs per side), amongst many. In 2019 she became the first woman to complete 20 years in cricket. She has a biopic on her lifestory - Shabaash Mithu in which Taapsee Pannu plays Mithali.\r\n', 'Mithali is also known as \"Lady Tendulkar of Indian Women\'s cricket\" because she has hit the most runs ever for India in all formats.', 'Profession', 'girl', 'All', 'Cricket, Sports', 'Slide52.PNG', 'proposed', '', 'book1'),
(53, 'P V Sindhu', 'P V Sindhu todo', 'Mirza is the third Indian woman to win a match at a major, and the first to advance past the second round.', 'sports', 'girl', 'all', 'shuttle, sports', 'Slide53.PNG', 'proposed', '', 'book1'),
(54, 'Amul Girl', 'Amul Girl is used to advertise the brand Amul. Amul is an Indian dairy company, making things like milk, butter, and even bread. The girl was made based on their rival companies “butter girl”, but became a massive hit.\r\n', 'Amul Girl is known as the best Indian advertisement because of its humor. \r\n', 'people, regional', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'Amul, butter, girl', 'Slide54.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(55, 'I love SILC boy', 'SILC, School of Indian Language and Culture is located in MN. From September to June, students can learn about their Indian heritage through language and many other classes. In the 2020-2021 school year SILC will, for the first time, be all online.', 'SIlC has been running for 52 years.', 'other', 'boy', 'NA', 'SILC, boys', 'Slide55.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Smriti', NULL),
(56, 'I love SILC Girl', 'SILC, School of Indian Language and Culture is located in MN. From September to June, students can learn about their Indian heritage through language and many other classes.', 'SIlC has been running for 52 years.', 'other', 'girl', 'NA', 'SILC, girls', 'Slide56.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(57, 'Kurta Pajama ', 'This dress is one of the most common dresses worn by young boys and men all over India. The top usually extends all the way to the knees and the material depends on the formality of the event. Usually the material is plain cotton, but during formal events, like marriage, silk or brocade with embroidered detailing is a common sight.', 'The Kurta Pajama dated to a 1015 AD in east India/Bihar.', 'Regional', 'boy', 'All', 'Formal, Simple, Traditional', 'Slide57.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(58, 'Bhagat Singh', 'Bhagat Singh was a folk hero of the Indian Revolutionary movement. He participated in 2 violent protests/boycotts against the British. His protest group killed British soldiers and then escaped from punishments, helping the Indian side in many ways during the revolution. ', 'His bravery is the reason people admire him.', 'regional, people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'Punjab', 'hats, turban, patriotism', 'Slide58.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(59, 'Abdul Kalam ', 'This suit is worn by missile scientist and former president of India Abdul Kalam. He was a very charismatic personality. He wrote many books, out of which \"Wings of Fire\" is the most well read. He came from a humble background and went on to occupy the highest office in India.', 'He is known as \"missile man of India\"', 'author', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide59.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(60, 'Alluri Sita Rama Raju', 'Alluri Sitarama Raju was an Indian Telugu revolutionary involved in the Indian independence movement. He was known to wear dhoti, a cloth wrapped around his chest, and to carry a bow and arrow.', 'He was referred to as \"Manyam Veerudu\" (\"Hero of the Jungle\") by the local people.', 'Other', 'boy', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Independence, Dhoti, patriotism', 'Slide60.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(61, 'Gopal Krishna Gokhale', 'Gopal Krishna Gokhale was a prominent social reformer during the Indian Independence movement. He was born to a Maharashtrian family. He was a contemporary of Bal Gangadhar Tilak and other Independence struggle visionaries. ', 'Gokhale fought relentlessly on behalf of the common man for better political representation and power over public affairs.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Maharashtra', 'dhoti, kurta, gandhi, cap, white, hats, turban, patriotism', 'Slide61.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(62, 'Fisherman', 'The Fishing Industry in Goa is very prominent so you can see fishermen all over. Young boys are generally sent with their older family members to fish at age 10. There are hundreds of types of fish they catch, and there are different methods to catching each. Boys learn at a young age so many of them are experts by the time they are adults.', 'There are many ways of trapping fish including the stick, barrier, caste gill and luring methods.', 'regional, people', 'boy', 'Goa', 'fish, fishing', 'Slide62.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(63, 'Farmer (male)', 'Men working in the fields typically wear simple, white, cotton clothes. These consist of a thin upper garment and loose pants or a dhoti. The white reflects the sun and keeps them cool during the hot summer days. The undyed clothing is also much cheaper and affordable.', 'The main crops grown for export in in India are wheat, pulses, millets, maize.', 'regional', 'boy', 'NA', 'hats, white', 'Slide63.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(64, 'Dandia Dress (male)', 'The male Dandia dress consists of dhoti-like pants, and a long shirt which sometimes flares near the waist. A longer cloth is wrapped around the head and/or waist for a festive look. Dandia dance form is native to Gujarat and is a significant part of the Dussehra festival. It is played with a pair of sticks in a synchronous and graceful manner.', 'Dandia dates back to ancient times where it used to be a learning component during footworks practice for swordfight. ', 'Dance, Occasional', 'boy', 'All', 'Dandia, sticks', 'Slide64.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(65, 'Bhangra Dancer (male)', 'Bhangra is a popular type of Dance originating in Punjab. The male costume consists of a kurti (a long shirt), chadar (a decorated cloth tied around the waist), and a Pag (turban). All elements of the costumes are made of light yet shimmery silken material. The Chadar and Pag may have additional embellishments or embroidery along their borders.', 'Bhangra contests have been organized in Punjab for many decades.', 'regional, dance', 'boy', 'Punjab', 'hats, turban, Bhangra, colorful', 'Slide65.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(66, 'Pahadi Girl', 'The word Pahad means hill or mountain in Hindi. In the sub-continent, Pahadi people  live in the Himalayan area which covers the states of Jammu, Kashmir, Himachal Pradesh, and Uttarakhand. Pahadi women are extremely hardworking people and have adapted to the harsh living conditions of the mountains. They often rely on growing their own crops for sustenance.', 'Pahadi people have their own language and a very distinct, colorful culture!', 'regional', 'girl', 'Uttarakhand', 'Pahari, pahadi', 'Slide66.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(67, 'Toda Tribe (woman)', 'Located in the mountains in the Nilgiris of Tamil Nadu, the Toda People have their own style of clothing. For women, a single piece of cloth is wrapped around the shoulders and torso like a shawl with a skirt as the bottom. The women also have another shawl that they use as well. Traditionally, the dress is red and black vertical stripes.', 'Most Toda people herd cattle or do dairy work and their community is very self-sufficient.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Tamilnadu', 'Toda, skirt, women', 'Slide67.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(68, 'Toda Tribe (man)', 'The Toda tribe are a Dravidian ethnic group who live in the Nilagiris mountains in Tamil Nadu. The traditional male dress consists a single piece of cloth that is worn across the chest like a shawl wrap. A dhoti is worn on the bottom.', 'People of the Toda Tribe are strict vegetarians!', 'Tribal', 'boy', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Dravidian, Nilagiris, Shawl, Dhoti', 'Slide68.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(69, 'Himachal Pradesh (woman)', 'The women of Himachal Pradesh wear long Kurtas stretching from their neck to their toe. They also wear Ghaghris, Salwar-Kameez and Cholis. In addition the women wear many pieces of jewelry including Chakk (head piece), Chanderhar (necklace), Toke (wristbands), and Pari (anklets).', 'It is cultural in Himachal Pradesh for the men to wear a turban and the women a shawl over their heads. This also keeps them warm in the cold climate.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'kurta, jewlery, Himalayas, anklets', 'Slide69.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(70, 'Dhoti Salwar', 'A dhoti salwar is a type of sarong that resembles American trousers. It is made from a long singular piece of fabric and then tucked through the legs and tied in the back or front. It is very simple to make and comfortable to wear. \r\n', 'A dhoti itself can be worn by both men and women!\r\n', 'people', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'salwar, dhoti, dresses', 'Slide70.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(71, 'Party Wear', 'Similar to an Anarkali, the Cascading Suit dress is one type of party wear. The skirt of the dress has pleats creating the cascading look and sometimes has an uneven bottom hem. The colors are most always bright and vibrant. The trends of party wear change from season to season, but the bright colors are one constant.', 'This is a common style to wear at Weddings.', 'festivals, dresses', 'girl', 'NA', 'dress, women, party', 'Slide71.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Smriti', NULL),
(72, 'Party Wear (children)', 'An outfit that is worn to parties in India by younger girls is a frock, or simple dress. This is usually matched with a headband, sandals, and some jewelry. ', 'The traditional frock dress is nearly 200 years old!', 'Fancy dress, Occasion', 'girl', 'All', 'Frock, dress, headband, sandals', 'Slide72.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(73, 'Maratha Dress', 'A Maratha Dress \nincludes a Pehta (hat), a Dhoti, a Kurta (cotton shirt), and a Bandi (waistcoat). The Pehta was intended to protect men from the sun during hot sunny days while the Bandi is only worn occasionally for formal events.', 'Many of the traditional attires in Maharashtra were influenced by the fact that the majority of people worked in agriculture.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Maharashtra', 'hats, turban, kurta, agriculture', 'Slide73.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(74, 'Salwar Kameez', 'The Salwar Kameez is the most commonly worn outfit in the Asian subcontinent. It is worn both for daily purposes as well as for formal or festive occasions.', 'Salwar Kameez is worn by both men and women.', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide74.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(75, 'Crop Top', 'The versatile crop tops are not restricted to be worn with lehengas alone but are also dressed up with sarees and dhoti pants. Crop tops and lehengas are ruling the Indian wedding chart and are a go-to outfit for most of the bridesmaids and even the contemporary brides. Crop Tops can be dressed down for a more relaxed look of necessary.', 'The Crop Top & Lehenga is the latest Indian Wedding Trend!', 'Dresses, regional', 'girl', '(Kashmir) North India', 'Women, Dresses, Formal, Simple, Traditional', 'Slide75.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(76, 'Shambo Cap', 'Shambo Cap is traditional tall cap headpiece worn by men in the Sikkim region, predominantly the Bhutia and Lepcha tribes.  The cap comes in different shades of red, yellow, and blue. It also comes in different patterns and designs.', 'It can also be worn by women!', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Sikkim', 'Hat, Shambo, Cap', 'Slide76.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(77, 'Half-Saree', 'A half saree is a traditional outfit that is extremely prominent in South India. This outfit, also called Langavoni, has three main components that include the skirt, called the Langa, which is tied around the waist with a string, a blouse, and a voni, a long cloth tied around the Langa and draped over the shoulder.', 'A Half-saree function is a coming of age ceremony in which a girl wears a Half-Saree for the first time.', 'Regional', 'girl', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'traditional, Langa, saree, ', 'Slide77.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(78, 'Subhash Chandra Bose', 'Subhash Chandra Bose was an Indian nationalist and freedom fighter. His patriotism made him a hero among the masses. He was one of the first leaders of the Indian National Congress. He was one of the stalwarts of the Indian freesom struggle and was known for being more aggressive in his approach in dealing with the British.', 'Bose was given the title \"Netaji\", which means Respected Leader', 'people, author', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'hats, turban, patriotism', 'Slide78.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(79, 'Maharashtra Pagidi', 'A pagidi is essentially a turban. The style that it is worn in and the color of the fabric are changed according to the occasion. For example saffron indicates valor and white indicates peace. People of all castes and social circles wear the pagidi. ', 'A Pagidi is a symbol of honor in all cultures in which it is worn.', 'festivals', 'boy', 'Maharashtra', 'hats, turban', 'Slide79.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(80, 'Bal Gangadhara Tilak', 'Bal Gangadhara Tilak was an Indian teacher and independence activist. He was known to wear a white kurta and dhoti, and sometimes a matching shawl as well. He also carried a cane as shown in the picture, and a red turban. This hat and outfit is a Maharashtran style dress, since he was from the state of Maharashtra. ', 'Bala Gangadhara Tilak is known as \"The father of Indian unrest.\"', 'Other, author', 'boy', 'Mahrashtra.', 'Independence, Shawl, Turban, patriotism', 'Slide80.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(81, 'Dabbawala', 'Dabbawalas constitute a lunchbox delivery system that delivers hot lunches from homes and restaurants to people at work in India. Dabbawalas are easily recognized by their white kurtas and Gandhi cap. They also can usually be found riding a bicycle. ', 'Dabbawalas have been delivering food for over 125 years and have been featured in a Harvard Business School Case Study!', 'Profession ', 'boy', 'Mumbai', 'hats, turban, kurta, catering, delivery', 'Slide81.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(82, 'Indian Prince', 'Different areas of India were all once ruled by Kings and Queens. These royalties children were princes. Because of the activities like sword fighting, princes would wear appropriate attire for that. The trousers were more for fighting, while the turbans were because they were royal.\r\n', 'Most princes would wear the shoes with the pointy tips! These were called mojari’s. \r\n\r\n', 'people, regional', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'prince, king', 'Slide82.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(83, 'VeshTi', 'The Lungi is worn mostly by south Indian men, but it is also worn in the northern states. This is usually worn in and around the home as it is very casual wear. However, the lungi can be dressed up and is worn as a traditional wear for festivals in the south Indian states of Tamil Nadu, Kerala, Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh, and Telangana', 'In southern states of India, a formal dhoti is called a mundu or a veshti. An informal dhoti is called a lungi.', 'casual wear', 'boy', 'Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Kerala, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Maharashtra, Goa, Odisha, West Bengal, Pu', 'Men, Lungi, Casual wear', 'Slide83.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(84, 'Dhothi', 'Dhoti is a type of sarong, that represents trousers. It is made out of a single rectangle shaped cloth, and made to be fitted and the waist and ankles, but otherwise very loose. It is the traditional lower garment worn by boys and men across India. It is commonly paired with a kurta or similar shirt on top.', 'The dhoti is also known as panche, vesti, dhuti, mardani, chaadra, dhotar, and panchey.', 'Occasion', 'boy', 'All', 'Dhoti, sarong', 'Slide84.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(85, 'Gandhi Dhothi', 'One of the most inspiring freedom fighters in the world, Gandhi is known to wear a simple white Dhothi (cloth) draped around his body. Many believe he decided to wear a Dhothi after seeing impoverished communities  and wanting to represent their struggles and hardships.  ', 'Gandhi sewed his own clothes in an act of resistance against British forces. ', 'people', 'boy', 'Gujurat', 'Gandhi, freedom, dhothi, patriotism', 'Slide85.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(86, 'Jaisalmer Dress', 'Jaisalmer is a very colorful city in Western Rajasthan. Due to the heat, the locals wear loose garments, but colorful. ', 'The Jaisalmer dress is worn along with the headpiece or turban.', 'dresses, festivals', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'Jaisalmer, dresses', 'Slide86.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(87, 'Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan ', 'Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan was famous for his work on religion and philosophy and for his time as a teacher at Oxford University. He was also a former president of India. His style of wearing a turban is symbolic of his work and he greatly influenced education in india.', 'In India, on September 5 each year, teachers day is celebrated . This is in honor of Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan as Sept. 5 is his birthday.', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'NA', 'hats, turban', 'Slide87.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(88, 'Sardar Vallabhai Patel', 'Sardar Patel was one of the most iconic figures of the Indian Freedom Struggle. Alongside Mahatma Gandhi and Jawaharlal Nehru and other stalwarts, he fought for the rights of the Indians under British rule, and eventually for freedom from the British. He was known as the Iron man of India because of his foresight and clarity in vision for the country', 'The Statue of Unity is a monument dedicated to Sardar Patel ', 'author', 'boy', '', 'patriotism', 'Slide88.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(89, 'Kerala Mundu ', 'Mundu is a traditional piece of attire in Kerala. The lower garment Mundu is a white cloth wrapped around the waist. It has a border called Kara which can be of any color but usually is golden. The upper garment is called Melmundu which is worn on the shoulders.', 'In Kerala, many people will be dressed in white attire because it signifies purity and elegance. ', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Kerala', 'Lungi, gold, white', 'Slide89.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(90, 'Pathan Dress', 'Pathan outfits are worn by men, and have been around for very many years. Because of the cloth, they are best worn in hot climates or in the summertime. They appear very graceful and are ideal when wanting to look nice. \r\n', 'They are said to have originated in Afghanistan, but are mostly worn in Punjab. \r\n', 'regional', 'boy', 'Punjab', 'pathan', 'Slide90.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(91, 'Dhoti and Lalchi', 'Wearing the dhoti and lalchi is more casual than party wear. The Dhoti is the bottom made of a cloth wrapped around the legs and through the middle to make a sort of pant. It is worn with a long shirt known as the lalchi. This is usually worn in and around the home by men.', 'A dhoti can be worn in almost all seasons in India.', 'other', 'boy', 'NA', 'dhoti, men, lalchi', 'Slide91.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(92, 'Shorts (boy)', 'Shorts are a shortened version of trousers. For boys, they can be assigned to wear as part of the school uniform, or sports uniforms. Shorts are also worn casually in the summertime, with a t-shirt.', 'Shorts are not just worn in India, but by millions across the world!', 'Other', 'boy', 'All', 'Shorts, Summertime', 'Slide92.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(93, 'Air India Maharaja', 'To distinguish itself from competing airlines, Air India created a mascot known as the Air India Maharaja. He is known for his vibrant red attire and turban. Although he can be seen in other dresses in advertisements, this is the attire he is most known for.', 'Air India Maharaja has been around for 56 years!', 'Profession', 'boy', 'All', 'hats, turban, red, mascot, airlines', 'Slide93.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(94, 'Vivekananda', 'Swami Vivekananda was an Indian philospher, author, and religious teacher. He was the disciple of Ramakrishna Paramahamsa.  He was a huge reason of the revival of Hinduism in India. He also contributed to Indian nationalism during the Revolution.', 'The speech given by Swami Vivekanand in Chicago in 1893 is considered to be one of the most famous speeches in history.', 'religious, author', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'swami, monk', 'Slide94.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL);
INSERT INTO `dresses` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `did_you_know`, `category`, `type`, `state_name`, `key_words`, `image_url`, `status`, `notes`, `book`) VALUES
(95, 'Ambedkar', 'B.R. Ambedkar was an economist, professor, and lawyer. He was also known for his campaigns against social discrimination towards the untouchables who were the lowest caste in India. The untouchables were people who did most of the dirty work in cleaning and sweeping the streets and bathrooms. They were treated as less than people, but Ambedkar raised their living standards. ', 'Ambedkar  has PHDs from both  Columbia University and the London School of Economics.', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'All', 'men, people, patriotism', 'Slide95.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Smriti', NULL),
(96, 'Tricolor Dress (Man)', 'Tricolor dresses in India can be any style, but must be consisting of the colors saffron, green and white. These are also the colors of the Indian flag.', '', 'Other, Occasional', 'boy', 'All', 'India, Saffron, Green, White, Flag, Tricolor,  patriotism', 'Slide96.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(97, 'Palazzos', 'Palazzo pants , palazzo trousers, (Indian English: pantada) are long women\'s trousers cut with a loose, extremely wide leg that flares out from the waist. Palazzos can be worn with a variety of tops including kurtas and even t-shirts\r\n', 'The word Palazzo has Italian roots which point to a palatial building or a palace with a broad base and narrow top.', 'Occasional', 'girl', 'All', 'Formal, Informal, Palazzo, Trousers, Pantada', 'Slide97.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(98, 'Gharara', '  A gharara is a traditional Lucknow outfit. It is typically worn by Indian Muslim women. It includes wide legged pants, a kurti and a dupatta. They used to be worn as everyday clothes, but are now also worn for weddings and fancier events. A gharara is exactly the same as a sharara except it is worn with a shorter (mid thigh length) kameez/kurti and a dupatta. The traditional gharara requires around 12 metres of fabric.', 'The Gharara is typically worn only by girls!', 'dresses, regional', 'girl', 'Uttar Pradesh, Northern India', 'dress, gharara, wedding', 'Slide98.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(99, 'Long Kurti and Lehenga', 'This is a variation of the Lehenga Choli dress but the top is as long as a typical kurti. This dress has become more popular and in recent years some of these dresses are coming out as one pieces instead of the traditional top and bottom.', 'While the ghagra choli may be similar to the lehenga choli and long kurti and lehenga dresses, the lehenga is more commonly worn at parties and festivals.', 'occasional', 'girl', 'All', 'dress, lehenga, kurti, women', 'Slide99.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(100, 'Long Kurti', 'Long Kurti is identical to the regular kurti, except for that this one is floor length, and generally becomes wider and flares from the waist down. It can be made from many different fabrics, and in many different designs and patterns.', 'The kurti style tunic is worn all across the world!', 'Occasional, Fancy Dress', 'girl', 'All', 'Kurti, Long, Tunic', 'Slide100.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(101, 'Business Suit', 'The normal business attire for men is a button down shirt, trousers, and a jacket or suit coat depending on the formality of the meeting or industry.\nThe dress code for women in Indian Business has undergone a significant transformation. Today, women often wear pant-suits or a blouse and skirt. ', 'In earlier years women in business would wear traditional Indian clothes such as a salwar kameez or a simple saree.', 'Profession', 'girl', 'All', 'business, suit, formal, pant-suit, work', 'Slide101.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(102, 'Kalbelia Dancer', 'The Kalbelia style of dance is a traditional dance in Rajasthan. It is typical for women and men to dance to, as it is traditionally not taught to children. There is a lot of spinning in this style of dance. And it is known as the \"Dance of the serpents\". ', 'The dancers design their own costumes, and make them themselves!', 'regional, dances, dresses, people', 'girl', 'Rajasthan', 'kalbelia, dancer, dresses', 'Slide102.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(103, 'Dhimsa Dress ', 'Dhimsa is a style of dance performed in Araku Valley. Typically, the women from the AP Tribe form a chain of 15-20 people and dance in patterns of circles. The dress is tied at the shoulder and is worn for this dance. The dancers also carry a peacock feather in their hand and dress with nice jewelry.', 'There are 12 main variations of this dance.', 'dance', 'girl', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'dance, tribal, women, ', 'Slide103.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(104, 'Dimasa Dress', 'This Dimasa dress is worn by women in the state of Assam. The dress has many components. Rijamphain is a plain color cloth worn from chest to knees. Rigu is a lower garment that is usually made of lots of different colors. Rikhaosa is a shawl-like wrap, that is worn over the Rijamphain.', 'The state of Assam has a population of over 30 million people!', 'Regional', 'girl', 'Assam', 'Dimasa, Rijamphain, Rigu, Rikhaosa', 'Slide104.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(105, 'Jharkand Tribal Dress', 'Jharkhand has a rich tribal culture and a dynamic heritage of textiles and fabric. Women cover themselves in sarees. Wealthier women will adorn themselves in an ethnic Tussar silk saree manufactured in Jharkhand. The tribal clothing of women is known as a Panchi Parhan. Panchi being the lower garment and Parhan the upper. The tribe-centric culture of Jharkhand prefers plain but elegant accessories including gold, silver, and beaded ornaments. ', 'Jharkhand is known as Vanachal, meaning the land of the woods.', 'tribal', 'girl', 'Jharkand', 'saree, textiles, gold, tribal', 'Slide105.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(106, 'Capri', 'Capris are simply shorter versions of pants. They are nice to wear in hotter weather because of the shorter length. They can be worn by both men and women, and are a bit longer than “shorts”. Capris are worn across the globe, not just in India. \r\n', 'Indian capris can be fancier than most other types, because there are many fabrics, designs, etc, that are used. \r\n', 'dresses', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'causual', 'Slide106.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(107, 'Harem Pants', 'Harem Pants are known as the western version of the dhoti (middle eastern and Indian baggy pants) and the Turkish Salvar. Paul Poiret introduced them to the west around 1910. They are similar to the trendy palazzo pants. ', 'Earlier, when they were first introduced they were originally called Harem Skirts.', 'casual', 'girl', 'All', 'pants,\ndhoti, salvar, western, palazzo, unisex', 'Slide107.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(108, '3/4 Skirt', 'The 3/4 skirt is a long skirt worn by women that runs from the waist to just above the ankles. It is 3/4 the length of a full length skirt, hence the name. It can be of plain color or many colors. It can also have minimal designs, or very intricate designs. ', 'This style skirt can be worn with many different types of tops and shirts!', 'Fancy dress', 'girl', 'All', 'skirt, 3/4', 'Slide108.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(109, 'Panchi Par', 'The Santals are one of the most populous tribal communities in India. The santali women wear colorful sarees that have a checkered pattern on the body and stripes on the pallu. Now a days, the sarees come with motifs of birds fishes, flowers, leaves, and animals. Generally the sarees have motifs on the pallu and sometimes on the borders. ', 'The Santals are mainly found in certain districts of Odisha but can also be found in the neighboring states of Jharkhand, West Bengal, Bihar, and Assam.', 'tribal', 'girl', 'Odisha, Jharkhand, West Bengal Bihar, Assam', 'saree, stripes, checkers, motifs, colorful', 'Slide109.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(110, 'Radhika Menon', 'Radhika Menon is an Indian Merchant Navy Officer who is currently serving as the captain of the Indian Merchant Navy. She was born in Kodungallur, Kerala. Menon has completed a radio course at the All India Marine College, Kochi. She had a short stint with Shipping Corporation of India, she became a prominent cadet of the Indian Navy. In 2012, she became the first ever female captain of the Indian Merchant Navy. Menon won accolades for rescuing seven fishermen who were trapped in the Bay of Bengal. She also took charge of the oil tanker, Suvarna Swarajya. \r\n', 'She also became the first woman to receive the IMO Bravery Award.', 'regional', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'navy, dress', 'Slide110.PNG', 'proposed', 'What is IMO?', 'book1'),
(111, 'Kiran Bedi', 'Kiran Bedi is an Indian social activist and was the 24th Liuetenant Governor of Pondicherry. From a young age, she participatted in the NCC and cleared the 10th grade matriculation exam when her classmates were in 9th. Inspired by her father, she started playing tennis and cut her hair short. She won many national tournaments and emerged as a champion. She then changed her focus from tennis and cleared the IPS exam. She is also well known for reforming the Tihar jail.  \r\n', 'She is the first woman of India to join the officer ranks of the IPS.\r\n', 'police', 'girl', 'ALL', 'khaki, uniform, officer, police, cap, pin, badge', 'Slide111.PNG', 'proposed', 'TODO: Indira Gandhi\'s car', 'book1'),
(112, 'Avani Chaturvedi', 'Avani Chaturvedi is an Indian pilot from Rewa, Madhya Pradesh. She along with two of her colleagues, Mohana Singh and Bhawana Kanth were inducted into the Indian Air Force. She competed her Bachelors in Technology from Banasthali University, Rajasthan in 2014. Avani, along with Singh and Kanth became the first female Indian fighter pilot. She also became the first Indian woman pilot to take a solo flight in a MiG-21. She was awarded with the Nari Shakti Puraskar in 2020.\r\n', 'In 2023, Avani became the first woman fighter pilot of the Indian Air Force to take part in an aerial wargame abroad, which she did in Japan.', 'profession', 'girl', 'All', 'Air force, pilot, medals', 'Slide112.PNG', 'proposed', '', 'book1'),
(113, 'Army Uniform', 'The Indian army uniform is a light and dark green camouflage color. There is also a matching cap, but that cap can be different styles and color based on officer ranking. All army members wear similar heavy duty black boots, and generally carry a firearm (depending on rank). On all uniforms there is an Indian army insignia, along with ranking pins for higher officials that go on the upper sleeves of the official.', 'India currently has 1.4 million active people in the army!', 'profession', 'girl', 'ALL', 'army, officer, official, camouflage, firearm ', 'Slide113.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(114, 'Doctor', 'Doctors in India generally wear a white lab coat. For women, this can be worn over a saree or comfortable clothing of their choice (depending on where they\'re working). For men, the coat can be worn over some dress pants and shirt. Generally a stethoscope or other personal medical equipment is kept with the outfit.\r\n\r\nNurses generally wear regular medical scrubs, or in some places, women wear a white top with a knee length white skirt. \r\n\r\nMore recently, it has become common and advised for both nurses and doctors to wear medical masks as part of their daily uniform.', 'There are over 900 thousand allopathic doctors in India!', 'doctor', 'girl', 'ALL', 'doctor, nurse, lab coat, scrubs, white, stethoscope, masks', 'Slide114.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(115, 'Anna Chandy', 'TODO', 'Anna Chandy (1905–1996), was the first female judge (1937) and then High Court judge (1959) in India. She was, in fact, one of the first female judges in the British Empire.', 'occupational', 'girl', 'All', 'lawyer, women, black, dress code', 'Slide115.PNG', 'proposed', '', NULL),
(116, 'Garima Arora', 'Garima Arora is an Indian Michelin star chef. She was brought up in Mumbai and is from a Punjabi Arora family. She studied at Le Corden Bleu, Paris and graduated in 2010. She has worked with famous chefs such as Gordon Ramsay, René Redzepi, and Gaggan Anand before openeing her own restaurant, Gaa in Bangkok in 2017. In 2018, Gaa won the Michelin star award and Garima became the first Indian woman to have a Michelin star. She is also a reknowned judge on the TV show, MasterChef. \r\n', 'Gaa has been named no. 16 on Asia\'s 50 Best Restaurants list in 2019.\r\n', 'proffesion', 'girl', 'All', 'chef, hat, food', 'Slide116.PNG', 'proposed', '', 'book1'),
(117, 'Mamata Benerjee', 'Mamata Benerjee is an indian politician currently serving as the 8th Chief Minister of West Bengal. Since 2011 when she was elected as the first woman to hold office, she founded the party All India Trinamool Congress (AITC). Mamata Benerjee is known for wearing simple white cotton sarees with a narrow mono-colored border. These sarees are made at Dhanekhali, a place renowned for its weaving.', 'Mamata Benerjee is often referred to as Didi meaning elder sister in Hindi and Bengali.', 'Profession', 'girl', 'West Bengal', 'politician, simple, saree, white', 'Slide117.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(118, 'Erukala Sani', 'Erulaka Sani is a fictional fortune teller from stories from Telugu speaking Indian states. She appears in many stories, and tells people what is to come in their futures or what luck they have. \r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Many kids love the stories involving her\r\n', 'regional, people', 'girl', 'Telugu States', 'erukala, sani, fortune', 'Slide118.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(119, 'Jayalalithaa', 'Jayalalithaa  was an Indian politician and film actress. She is known for starring in over 140 films. Later, she would become the Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu. She was both very popular as well as controversial during her term. She achieved many successful schemes for babies and mothers.', 'She is known in the film industry as the  \"Queen of Tamil Cinema\"', 'people', 'girl', 'Tamil Nadu', 'people, women, actress, Chief Minister', 'Slide119.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(120, 'Dokhona ', 'Dokhona is the traditional dress worn by the Bodo tribe woman in the state of Assam. It is similar to a saree, but the cloth is cut a little more wide, and it is wrapped differently.', 'The Bodo tribe is known to be over 3000 years old!', 'Tribal', 'girl', 'Assam', 'Bodo, Dokhona, Assam', 'Slide120.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(121, 'Koch-Rajbongshi', 'The Koch-Rajbongshi Traditional Dress for women in Assam. It includes a cotton cloth called a Patani that is roughly 5 feet in length and wrapped around the body. Younger women and girls wear two pieces of shorter cloth called Agran. The colors of the cloth may vary but are predominantly yellow, red, and green. Ornaments such as earrings, nose rings, anklets, bracelets and necklaces are also worn. ', 'There are 15 different types of Patani (cloth wrapped around the body in traditional Koch-Rajbongshi dresses).', 'tribal', 'girl', 'Assam, Meghalaya, North Bengal, and Bihar ', 'colorful, yellow, ornaments, traditional, tribal', 'Slide121.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(122, 'Sharara', 'Shararas are typically South Asian dresses.  Sharara is a pair of loose, flared, and wide-legged trousers mostly worn with straight kurti.', 'The Sharara can be traced back to the Mughal era!', 'dresses, regional', 'girl', 'Uttar Pradesh, Northern India', 'dress, sharara, wedding', 'Slide122.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(123, 'Shawl', 'The Kashmiri Shawl is identified by its Kashmiri weave. Many Kashmiri shawls are also made of fine shahtoosh or pashmina wool. They tend to have exquisite detailing on the edges and take a lot of time and effort to make.', 'A single shawl takes fleece from up to three goats.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Kashmir', 'Kashmiri, Shawl, handmade', 'Slide123.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(124, 'Army (Woman)', 'The Indian army uniform is a light and dark green camouflage color. There is also a matching cap, but that cap can be different styles and color based on officer ranking. All army members wear similar heavy duty black boots, and generally carry a firearm (depending on rank). On all uniforms there is an Indian army insignia, along with ranking pins for higher officials that go on the upper sleeves of the official.', 'India currently has 1.4 million active people in the army!', 'profession', 'girl', 'All', 'Army, camouflage, officer, official, firearm', 'Slide124.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(125, 'Bandgala Jacket', 'A Jodhpur suit or bandhgala jacket is a formal suit from India. It was popularized in the mid 19th century in India. It consists of a coat and trousers sometimes accompanied by a vest. Usually made out of silk, the suits may also have lining at the collar and at the buttons with embroidery. It is suitable for occasions such as weddings and formal gatherings. ', 'Traditionally the coat matched the trousers but now the trend is to wear contrasting colors.', 'occasional', 'boy', 'Rajasthan', 'suit, formal, weddings, vest, coat', 'Slide125.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(126, 'Modi Jacket', 'The Modi Jacket is the typical dress Prime Minister Narendra Modi wears on a regular basis during his events. It consists of a kurta and a vest. What is unique to him is the half sleeve kurta. They are generally made of silk or fine cotton.', 'Modi gets his attire made in the fine shops of Gujrat!', 'people, author', 'boy', 'India', 'Modi, vest', 'Slide126.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(127, 'Modi Kurta', 'The Modi Kurta is very similar to the regular Kurta, but has shorter sleeves compared to the full sleeves of the regular Kurta.  These sleeves are only half cut or three fourths but are longer than the traditional tee-shirt sleeves.', 'Prime Minister Narendra Modi created this and many other fashion trends.', 'people', 'boy', 'All', 'Kurta, Modi, ', 'Slide127.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(128, 'Gujarati Kediyu ', 'The Kediyu is a garment worn by men in the state of Gujarat. It is traditionally a long-sleeved upper garment that is pleated at the chest. It is worn with chorno, or kafni, which are like trousers that are wide and tied loosely at the ankles. The intricate designs on these dresses are only found in the state of Gujurat.', 'This dress is based on styles worn in Iraq in the 7th century!', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Gujurat', 'Kediyu, Chorno, Kafni', 'Slide128.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(129, 'BuDa Bukkala', 'The Budabukkala is a community that has been designated an Other Backward Class in Andhra Pradesh since 1993. They are a nomadic tribe that teaches morality to people through mythological aspects. In one hand they carry a lantern and in the other a small two-headed drum known as a Damarukam. They wear 4 layers of clothes and tie a long cloth around their head like a turban. They are known to grow long mustaches and wear large bindis on their foreheads. ', 'Unlike most tribes, they go looking for alms at night rather than during the day. ', 'regional, tribal', 'boy', 'Tamil nadu, Kerala, Andhra Pradesh', 'hats, turban, drum, mustache, mythology', 'Slide129.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(130, 'Sherwani', 'Sherwani is the most exclusive attire for Indian men. It is the ethnic Indian attire for men and with the advent of Indian fashion designers, the sherwani has turned into the most exquisite piece of male Indian garments.', 'Sherwani for men is a symbol of rich and traditional fashion with a touch of royal attitude and sophistication.', 'Religious, North India, Hindu', 'boy', 'Rajasthan', 'Formal, Traditional', 'Slide130.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(131, 'P C Sorcar', 'Protul Chandra Sorcar was an Indian magician. He performed internationally live and on television  throughout the 1950s and 1960s. His turban is an iconic symbol of both him, and other magicians as he changed how the Westerners viewed Indians for the better.', 'He is very well known for the \"Water of India\" trick.', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'Bangladesh', 'hats, turban, magicians, men, people', 'Slide131.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(132, 'Chef (Male)', 'Chefs are professionals who work in restaurants or hotels. Most chefs have education that qualifies them to work for hotels. For example, Hotel Management is a popular degree.', 'Vikaas Khanna and Sanjeev Kapoor are a few of the most successful Indian chefs!', 'proffesion', 'boy', 'All', 'hats, chef, food', 'Slide132.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(133, 'Lawyer (Male)', 'Male lawyers in India wear a black button up coat, in the form of a chapkan (a long coat), achkan (knee length jacket, or sherwani (long coat like top) with white bands and an advocates gown. ', 'There are approximately 1.2 million lawyers in India plus 400,000 to 500,000 more studying law at any given moment. ', 'profession', 'boy', 'all', 'law, formal, coat, black, gown', 'Slide133.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(134, 'Doctor (Male)', 'Doctors will normally wear a white coat over their regular clothes. For men, it can be over a normal shirt and pants or a suit shirt and more formal pants. Doctors may wear a stethoscope around their neck for easier access, or carry a mask and gloves with them. \r\n', 'The doctor ratio is very small compared to the population of India, which makes this profession one is dire need of more people. ', 'people', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'male doctor', 'Slide134.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(135, 'Fire Fighter (Male)', 'Firemen wear helmets and fire-protective gear when on the job. In India, firemen wear either a khaki colored uniform or a navy colored uniform. They carry many items such as an oxygen tank, radio, axe, head lamp and other personal protective equipment. All of these can cost upwards of 10000 dollars per fireman and weigh upwards of 75 pounds.', 'Firemen need at least 6 months of training before they are ready to work full time.', 'occupational', 'boy', 'All', 'work, men, firefighter', 'Slide135.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Smriti', NULL),
(136, 'CISF (Girl)', 'CISF stands for the Central Industrial Security Force. It is an armed police force in India, set up in 1969. The uniform is very similar to the army. A long sleeved shirt and trousers are worn of the green camouflage color. This is paired with a matching hat and dark heavy duty boots. A firearm is also carried.', 'There are nearly 150,000 CISF members in India!', 'proffesion', 'girl', 'All', 'CISF, army, firearm', 'Slide136.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(137, 'Air Force Pilot (Male)', 'Male Air Force Pilots in India wear blue gray terry wool tunics with a silk rank braid on their sleeves. They have matching blue gray trousers and a full sleeve shirt with a plain black tie. They also have a navy blue hat and black shoes. Pilots with honorary medals will have them on their uniform as well as a name tag and proficiency badges.', 'The Indian Air Force motto is taken from the Bhagavad Gita and means \"touch the sky with glory.\"', 'profession', 'boy', 'all', 'uniform, air force, blue, pilot', 'Slide137.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(138, 'Home Guard', 'Indian Home Guards were men who volunteered to support the Union during the American Civil War. They fought for the Union side, defending the \"home\" and were recruited and sent to America during the time. Their attire consisted of the typical shirt and pants, a more heavy-duty type, suitable for battle.', 'The Union side had far more soldiers during the battle thanks to minority groups like Indians. This helped a lot because the Confederate side generally had better war time strategies and generals. ', 'regional', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'war, home guard, civi war', 'Slide138.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(139, 'Navy (Male)', 'The Indian Navy has 10 different uniforms in 3 different colors: White, Black and Navy. Men wear shirts and pants but are allowed to wear shorts in the summer if necessary. The navy has very specific guidelines on when to wear which uniform and all members are required to memorize those regulations.', 'For the Navy, the color White is symbolic of power and respect.', 'occupational', 'boy', 'All', 'Navy, uniform, men', 'Slide139.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(140, 'Business Suit (Male)', 'The business suit is commonly worn in a professional work setting. It is a button down shirt, of any color, with', '', 'Profession', 'boy', 'All', 'Business, Suit, Coat, Jacket', 'Slide140.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(141, 'C V Raman', 'Sir Chandrasekhara Venkata Raman was an Indian physicist who made ground breaking discoveries in light scattering.  \r\n\r\nNational Science Day is celebrated in India on 28 February each year to mark the discovery of the Raman effect by  Raman on 28 February 1928. For his discovery, C.V. Raman was awarded the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1930 and was the first Asian to receive a Nobel Prize in any branch of science!', 'Raman was the paternal uncle of Subrahmanyan Chandrasekhar, recipient of the 1983 Nobel Prize in Physics.', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', '', 'hats, turban, suit, physicist', 'Slide141.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(142, 'Phiran', 'The phiran dress is a traditional outfit that both men and women wear in Kashmir. It consists of 2 gowns on top of each other.  It can be made with cotton for summer and wool for winter.', 'Mughal emperor Akbar introduced this outfit in 1586, according to some sources!', 'regional, dresses', 'boy', 'Kashmir', 'phiran, kashmir, akbar, ', 'Slide142.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(143, 'Pittala Dora', 'Before movies were the main form of entertainment, Pittala Doras would be the comedic relief for small towns. The men would wear khaki colored clothing (dressed like a colonial policeman)and carry a piece of wood shaped like a gun. Their comedy revolves around exaggerating and false promises.', '', 'occupational', 'boy', '', 'hats, turban,\nguns, humor', 'Slide143.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Smriti', NULL),
(144, 'Himachal Pradesh (male)*', 'The male dress in the state of Himachal Pradesh consists of tight Churidar Pyjamas, with a Kurta and long overcoat on top. Occasionally the churidar is replaced with dhoti.  A circular cap is very common in the state, even worn to work and in day to day life.', 'Himachal Pradesh is home some of the most picturesque hill stations in India, including kulu Manali, Rohtang Pass, Dalhousie etc.', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Churidar Pyjamas, Kurta, Dhoti', 'Slide144.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(145, 'Lord Srikrishna', 'Lord Krishna is a major deity in Hinduism. He is worshipped as the eight avatar of the God Vishnu. He is the god of compassion, tenderness, love, and is one of the most popular and widely revered among the Indian divinities. Lord Krishna has blue skin and is usually depicted with a flute in his hand. He also wears a crown with a peacock feather on his head. ', 'There’s a story that says that once, Lord Krishna decided to play the flue in the forest. So melodious was his music that the peacocks were enamored and began to dance with him.', 'religious', 'boy', 'all', 'god, blue, peacock, flute', 'Slide145.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(146, 'Lord Sriram', 'In Hinduism, Lord Sriram (more commonly referred to as Ram or Rama) is the seventh avatar of Vishnu. He is considered to be one of the most virtuous heroes and is considered to symbolize purity. His attire consists of simple Indian pants and archery weapons.', 'He is notable for slaying the demon Ravana.', 'religious', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'rama, lord, sriram', 'Slide146.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(147, 'Lord Shiva', 'Lord Shiva is known as the \"destroyer\" in Hindu mythology. He wears a tiger skin and carries a trident.', 'He is known as the destroyer because he removes all evil from the world.', 'people', 'boy', 'All', 'Tiger, trident, Shiva', 'Slide147.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Smriti', NULL),
(148, 'Kashmiri Shawl\n\nBOY', 'Kashmiri Shawl is a type of shawl that can be identified by its distinctive Kashmiri weave and patterns, and it is made of very fine wool.', 'They are not only worn in Kashmir, but the style and design have become popular across the world.', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Kashmir', 'shawl', 'Slide148.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(149, 'Telangana Talli', 'Telangana Talli is a symbolic mother goddess for the people of Telangana. The goddess statue wears a red saree and crown while holding maize in one hand representing harvest and prosperity while in the other hand she holds Bathukamma, the unique cultural symbol of Telangana.', 'A new Telangana Talli statue is being designed and sculpted as a tribute to the first World Telugu Conference. ', 'regional', 'girl', 'Telangana', 'goddess, harvest, saree, mother, maize', 'Slide149.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(150, 'Mangal Pandey', 'Pandey was an Indian soldier. He was very important in the Indian Rebellion of 1857, and was even a sepoy in the British East India company. His bravery and actions are commended by Indians. His dress goes along with his role as a soldier.', 'The Indian government created a stamp with his face on it, in memory of him. ', 'people', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'soldier, stamp, patriotism', 'Slide150.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(151, 'Astronaut (Female)', 'Space suits are sometimes worn while inside the rocket but are mainly necessary when the astronaut goes outside into space. The suit is made to keep the wearer safe and comfortable while in harsh conditions. They are equipped with oxygen and many other systems to allow the wearer a full range of motion while in the bulky suit.', 'The first woman in space was Valentina Tereshkova.', 'occupational', 'girl', 'All', 'suit, space, women, heavy', 'Slide151.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(152, 'Astronaut (Male)', 'Astronauts are those who go to outer space, and to do so they must wear a spacesuit. Though it may be difficult to go in depth regarding each and every part of the spacesuit, they are designed to help astronauts breathe and work in space.', 'Rakesh Sharma was the first and (so far) only Indian to travel to space in 1984.', 'profession', 'boy', 'All', 'space, spacesuit, astronaut', 'Slide152.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(153, 'Sankaracharya', 'Adi Shankaracharya was an 8th-century Indian philosopher and theologian who consolidated the doctrine of Advaita Vedanta. He is credited with unifying and establishing the main currents of thought in Hinduism. He wrote copious commentaries on the Vedic canon (Brahma Sutras, Principal Upanishads and Bhagavad Gita) in support of his thesis. He established the importance of monastic life in a time monasticism was ridiculed. He is reputed to have founded four mathas (\"monasteries\"), which helped in the historical development, revival and spread of Advaita Vedanta.', 'Sankaracharya explained the key difference between Hinduism and Buddhism, stating that Hinduism asserts \"Atman (Soul, Self) exists\", while Buddhism asserts that there is \"no Soul, no Self.”\n\n\n', 'People', 'boy', 'Kerala', 'monestary, philosophy, hinduism', 'Slide153.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(154, 'Raja Rama Mohan Roy', 'Raja Rama Mohan Roy was one of the founders of Brahmo Sabha. He was also known as the \"father of Indian Renaissance\". He worked hard to abolish child marriage in India and the practice of sati. His attire consists of a red dress on top of an undershirt, and a scarf like shawl over his upper body. ', 'He was titled Raja by Akbar the second!', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'Bengal', 'raja, roy, brahmo sabha', 'Slide154.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(155, 'Jain Woman', 'There are two groups of Jains. One group wears clothes while the other does not. Jain women who wear clothes, wear ones that are not revealing of their figure or their skin. They wear white clothes as a symbol of their purity and peace. Other Jain women choose not to wear clothes at all as a symbol of their purity.', '0.07 percent of the world are Jains', 'regional', 'girl', 'Maharashtra, Rajasthan, Gujarat and Madhya Pradesh', 'Jainism, women, mask', 'Slide155.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(156, 'Jain Man', 'Jain men wear thin white robes. They usually go barefoot, as they like to live life with as little possessions as possible. It is also common for them to wear a face mask, to prevent them from accidentally inhaling tiny insects. ', 'There are nearly 6 million Jain people worldwide!', 'Other (religious)', 'boy', 'Rajasthan, Gujarat, All', 'Jain, robes, face mask', 'Slide156.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(157, 'Buddhist Monk', 'Buddhist monks wear simple robes generally in a yellow or orange color. They wear these robes to ward of heat, cold, flies, and for the simple means of covering their bodies. Monks also shave their heads to symbolize their commitment to the Holy Life. ', 'Monks wear orange robes because at the time, orange was the only color dye available. ', 'profession', 'boy', 'all', 'orange, robe, holy, simple, monk', 'Slide157.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(158, 'Parsi Woman', 'Parsi, is a member of a group of followers in India of the Persian prophet Zoroaster. Parsi women wear embroidered saris typically. Over the years the saris have evolved a lot. ', 'The sari they wear are called Ghara.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Gujrat', 'sari, parsi, ', 'Slide158.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(159, 'Parsi Man', 'A Parsi, is a member of a group of followers in India of the Persian prophet Zoroaster. These people migrated from persia during the muslim conquest of Persia. Traditionally these men wear their long caftan (kurti-like top), tied at the waist and a turban around the head. ', 'There are about 69,000 Parsis in India', 'regional', 'boy', 'Gujarat', 'hats, turban,', 'Slide159.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(160, 'Karakul Hat', 'The Karakul hat, also called the Jinnah cap, is made from the fur of the Qaraqul sheep. The hat is typically worn by muslim men, and most commonly in the Jammu and Kashmir region.', 'The Karakul hat originates from Afghanistan.', 'Regional, Other', 'boy', 'Jammu & Kashmir', 'hats, cap, Karakul, Jinnah, Qaraqul', 'Slide160.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(161, 'Muslim Boy', 'Muslim boys and men in India can be seen wearing a few common outfits. They mainly wear either a salwar kameez (long top) and sherwal (white cotton pants) or a thobe (ankle length robe). Either outfit may be topped with a turban or a ghutra (square head scarf) tied with a egal (a black rope band) to fasten it in place. ', 'Turbans can be very long, some ranging up to 10 feet!', 'religious', 'boy', 'all', 'hats, turban', 'Slide161.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(162, 'Kodava Dress', 'The Kodava dress for men is a white collared long sleeve shirt with a black more dress-like thing. They also wear a thick red belt around their waist.', 'Kodavas are the only Indians allowed to carry firearms without licenses.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Karnataka', 'kodava', 'Slide162.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(163, 'Badaga Dress', 'Men use a cloth known as \"mundu\" to cover themselves. They also use another thiner piece of the same cloth to make their turban. Women use two pieces of cloth to make their dress. ', 'Badaga tribal language called \"Badugu\".', 'regional', 'boy', 'Karnataka', 'hats, turban', 'Slide163.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(164, 'Saree Kurta', 'Saree Kurta is basically a long Kurta style tunic, with the dupatta or chunni worn like how a saree is wrapped. This is a much more recently invented dress, and can be worn at parties and function with jewelry and accessories.', 'This dress is worn across India!', 'Fancy Dress, Occasion', 'girl', 'All', 'Saree, kurta, tunic, dupatta, chunni', 'Slide164.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(165, 'Belly Dancer ', 'Belly Dancers are known for their vibrant costumes including a blouse, bell shaped bottoms, a skirt, a hip scarf, and often a headband or turban. Footwear is not required for belly dancing, but if worn, belly dancers choose soft ballet like shoes to protect their feet.', 'The term \"belly dance\" was actually a misunderstanding of \"Raks Beledi\" meaning country or native.', 'profession, dances', 'girl', 'all', 'dance, coins, jewelry ', 'Slide165.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(166, 'Peplum Kurti', 'A peplum kurti is a very simple upper body dress. It is a longer kurti that goes a little below the stomach. It can come with pants but can also be sold individually. They can be dressed up or casual, like with jeans. ', 'The name is similar to the Peplum in American dresses. ', 'dresses', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'peplum, casual', 'Slide166.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(167, 'Angrakha Suit', 'The Angrakha dress was originally worn only by men. It is set up similarly to a wrap dress. And once women started picking up the trend, the dress started adopting styles similar to the Salwar Kameez while still functionally being a wrap dress.', 'Angrakha, historically, were worn in the royal courts by members of royalty.', 'other', 'girl', 'all', 'dress, salwar', 'Slide167.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(168, 'Angrakha Suit', 'The Angrakha Suit refers to the upper garment worn by Hindu men in India. It looks similar to a kurta, but is really a (tailored) cloth that is tied or buttoned to the left or right side. Some styles of this ', 'In the olden days, this was a court outfit that a man could wrap around himself, and be comfortable.', 'Occasional, Regional, Other', 'boy', 'All', 'Angrakha, suit, kurta, tie, button', 'Slide168.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(169, 'Kaftan', 'A symbol of exoticism and lifestyle, over the years \"Kaftan\" has become the catchall term for any kind of loose-fitting robe or tunic. A true kaftan is a narrow cut, long robe with full sleeves, either with a deep neck or fully open to the floor. It can be made from almost any type of material most commonly silk, wool, or cotton and are often bound with a sash.', 'Kaftan is a Persian word and is believed to have originated in Ancient Mesopotamia ', 'regional, religious', 'boy', 'all', 'robe, long, ancient', 'Slide169.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(170, 'Lungi Skirt', 'A lungi skirt is a simple skirt made out of a long single piece of fabric. Lungis can be worn by men and women, but this type of skirt is for women. It is made by wrapping the skirt around and round and tying it till it is a skirt. ', 'Lungis are a very casual dress, mostly worn inside the home and not for outside. ', 'dresses', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'lungi, skirt, casual', 'Slide170.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(171, 'Goncha', 'The people of Ladakh wear a thick robe known as \"Goncha\" to keep themselves warm during the winter season. They may wear the goncha with a tipi (hat). Women can also wear a cloak and both men and women wear shawls and scarfs.', 'The language in Ladakh is Tibetan', 'regional', 'girl', 'Jammu and Kashmir', 'hats, turban, robe, goncha', 'Slide171.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(172, 'Ladakh man', 'Lakakh is a region in the Himalayan mountains that is administered by India as a union territory. Men usually wear a thick woolen robe', 'Ladakh is famous for its monasteries, landscapes, and lakes. ', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Ladakh', 'Himalayas, Goucha, Sash, Skerag', 'Slide172.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(173, 'Jama Jacket', 'The Jama Jacket was an ancient attire found in the Mughal Empire. Some styles of the jama were tight around the torso but flared out like a skirt to below the knees or ankles. Other styles, such as the chakman jama, ended around the knees. The sleeves tended to be full and the jama was tied to either side with strings. ', 'Jama Jackets were originally male dresses but they were adopted by females as well in later years.', 'regional', 'boy', 'all', 'hats, turban, Mughal empire, ancient, long, skirt', 'Slide173.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha ', NULL),
(174, 'Maxi Dress', ' A Maxi Dress is a long floor-length dress. It can be casual and formal. It is not necessarily an India specific dress, because it is worn in many different countries. ', 'There are many different fabrics and styles of a maxi dress. ', 'dresses', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'dress, maxi', 'Slide174.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(175, 'Jama Jacket', 'The Jama Jacket (influenced by Mughal Empire) is worn by both men and women. It is made to resemble sewn jackets worn in ancient Persia and has a tight bodice with full sleeves but flares out for a looser bottom.', 'It is meant to be worn as a blanket jacket.', 'regional', 'girl', 'all', 'jacket, blanket', 'Slide175.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(176, 'Punjabi Lungi', 'The Punjabi Lungi is also called tamba, or tehmat. It is the traditional lower garment worn in the state of Punjab. This cloth is folded at the front, and can come in plain colors or very fancy depending on the occasion. It is usually paired with a kurta, and a ', 'Punjab is home to \"Harmandir Sahib\" which is the holiest Sikh place of worship.', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Punjab', 'lungi, tamba, tehmat, kurta, dastar', 'Slide176.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(177, 'Tagore', 'Rabindranath Tagore, was a Bengali poet, writer, music composer, and painter from the Indian subcontinent. He reshaped Bengali literature and music, as well as Indian art with Contextual Modernism in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. He wrote the Lyrics for the National Anthem of India.', 'Tagore won the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1913!', 'people, author', 'boy', 'Bengal', 'poet, literature, music, artist, patriotism', 'Slide177.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(178, 'Baji Rao ', 'Baji Rao was a general of the Maratha empire. He served as Peshwa. He was an excellent warrior, and so his attire fit that role. Lots of armor was necessary to wear. ', 'Baji Rao never lost a battle in the 20+ years he fought. ', 'people, regional', 'boy', 'Maharastra', 'hats, turban, peshwa', 'Slide178.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(179, 'Lord Vishnu', 'Lord Vishnu is one of the 3 most important Gods in Hinduism. He is blue because he is described to be infinite and immeasurable, like the sky. In most renditions he is wearing garlands of flowers and golden yellow pants with a Sudarshan Chakra and a Gadda.', 'Lord Vishnu was reborn 10 times', 'people', 'boy', 'All', 'Vishnu, Hinduism, ', 'Slide179.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(180, 'Minister Birbal', 'Raja Birbal was the main commander in army during the rule of Mughal empire, Akbar. ', 'Birbal is in many folktales from his time. You can read them at: www.moralstories.org/tag/akbar-birbal.', 'Other', 'boy', 'All', 'Raja Birbal, commander, Mughal, Akbar', 'Slide180.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(181, 'Tenali Ramakrishna', 'Tenali Ramakrishna was an Indian poet, scholar, thinker and a special advisor in the court of Sri Krishnadevaraya who ruled from C.E. 1509 to 1529. He was a Telugu poet generally known for folk tales which focus on his wit. He was one of the Ashtadiggajas or the eight poets at the court of Krishnadevaraya, the Vijayanagara emperor.\n\n', 'Tenali Ramakrishna was also a great scholar of several languages that included Telugu, Kannada, Tamil, Hindi, Malayalam and Marathi.', 'People', 'boy', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'poet, wit, scholar, humor', 'Slide181.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(182, 'Baul Folk Singer (Male)', 'The music of the Baul people, Baul Sangeet is a type of folk music. The songs must only use two types of meter in the song and have an unmeasured introduction. Men typically wear orange kurtas and turbans. ', 'The music represents the long heritage of preaching mysticism. ', 'regional', 'boy', 'Bengal', 'baul', 'Slide182.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(183, 'Baul Folk Singer (Female)', 'The music of the Baul people, Baul Sangeet is a type of folk music. The songs must only use two types of meter in the song and have an unmeasured introduction. Female singers are known to wear orange colored sarees.', 'Originally, Bauls were those who rejected the social norms to live a free life.', 'regional', 'girl', 'West Bengal', 'saree, singing, folk', 'Slide183.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(184, 'Onapottan', 'Onapottan is a folk character. He appears during the Onam season in the state of Kerala. He wears props such as a heavy crown, umbrella, bangles, bell, and beard. Besides that, he comes barefoot, wearing a fancy piece of cloth wrapped around the waist.', '', 'Occasion', 'boy', 'Kerala', 'Onapottan, Onam, crown, umbrella, bell', 'Slide184.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(185, 'Theyyam', 'Theyyam is a ritualistic performance to worship gods. It\'s one of the oldest indigenous and mystic ritual art forms. The costumes are made of coconut sheaths that are painted black, white, and red. Fresh coconut fronds make up the skirts and a red cloth is tied around the waist. The costumes and facial makeup may vary by role and myth.\r\n', 'Theyyam roots can be traced back 1500 years!', 'regional, religious', 'boy', 'Kerala', 'ritual, red, coconut, myth, performance', 'Slide185.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(186, 'Santa Claus', 'Santa Claus is a fictional character who is said to pass out gifts with a magical sleigh on Christmas. He is present in Christian religions, rather than in Hindu. While Christianity is a minority religion in India, there are still many Christians in India who will talk about Santa. ', 'His red and white dress is unique to him.', 'religious, people', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'santa, presents, sleigh, reindeer', 'Slide186.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(187, 'Haridasu', 'Haridasus go from house to house and sing songs. Similar to carolers. A Haridasu will have a sort of a bowl on the top of his head and wear clothes with bright colors. They will also be carrying their instruments with them.', 'People believe that some songs sung by the Hari Dasu signify new beginnings.', 'occupational', 'boy', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'singing, music, men', 'Slide187.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(188, 'Burra Katha Artist', 'Burra Katha is an oral storytelling technique performed in Andhra Pradesh and Telangana. They can be both male and female and wear very traditional Indian clothing. In addition, they play tambura, wear anklets, and lots of jewelry.', 'Burra Katha was a pastime event in rural villages. Now it is used to tell tales such as the Ramayana and Mahabharata.', 'Regional, Other', 'boy', 'Andhra Pradesh, Telangana', 'Burra katha, storytelling, tambura, anklets', 'Slide188.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(189, 'China Poblana', 'The fashion design of the china poblana dress is attributed to Catarina de San Juan. Catarina de San Juan was  Born into an aristocratic Muslim family in Mughal India before she made the perilous journey to New Spain at a young age and transformed herself into a Counter-Reformation mystic. The china outfit is made up of the following garments: a white blouse, a skirt , a white slip, and a shawl. The china wearer completed the outfit with beads and jewels that adorned her ears and her hands.', 'China Poblana is the symbol of Mexican femininity', 'regional', 'girl', '', 'blouse, skirt, fancy, colorful, beads, jewelry', 'Slide189.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(190, 'Telugu Talli', 'Telugu Thalli is a symbol of the Telugu people. She holds a harvest in her left hand showing that there will always be greenery. In the right hand she holds the kalasam which signifies that she brings all good to people\'s lives. ', 'She is also called Mother Telugu', 'regional', 'girl', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'telugu, talli', 'Slide190.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(191, 'Bonalu Woman', 'Bonalu is a Dravidian traditional Hindu festival centered on the Goddess Mahakali. Women prepare a special rice and carry it to the temple in a brass pot lined with neem leaves on their head. Once reaching the temple, they will offer the rice to the Goddess. This was originally done to rid the cites of plague. ', 'The Bonalu festival is now also used as a way to empower women as  they participate in offering the Bonam at the temples.', 'festivals', 'girl', ' Telangana', 'festivals, offering, ', 'Slide191.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(192, 'Dungaree', 'Dungaree is a clothing word that originates from India. It is basically jean overalls. These are be worn by girls and women across the world with short or long sleeve shirts underneath.', 'Dungaree is also referred to denim cloth, the material that the outfit is made from. ', 'Other', 'girl', 'All', 'dungaree, denim, jenas, overalls', 'Slide192.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(193, 'Holi Girl', 'Holi is a popular ancient Hindu festival, also known as the festival of spring or the festival of colors. In celebrating this festival, powdered color is thrown or sprayed onto friends, family, and neighbors in the streets. For this occasion, people tend to wear white colored clothes to highlight the colors of the festival. The types of outfits are limitless as women will wear outfits ranging from kurtis to sarees to shirts with jeans. \r\n', 'The colors used in Holi all have significances to them. Red symbolizes love, yellow for turmeric, green for spring, and blue to represent Krishna.', 'occasional', 'girl', 'all', 'color, white, holi, spring, festival', 'Slide193.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL);
INSERT INTO `dresses` (`id`, `name`, `description`, `did_you_know`, `category`, `type`, `state_name`, `key_words`, `image_url`, `status`, `notes`, `book`) VALUES
(194, 'Holi Boy', 'Holi is a popular festival around India. It symbolizes the victory of good over evil, hence the many colors thrown during the games. The dress for this is anything you don\'t mind getting ruined. Holi colors can stain, and so many times Indians will wear simple white dresses so that it\'s okay if the dress gets stained. ', 'It is a popular holiday even among non-Hindus in India', 'religious, festivals', 'boy', 'India (all over)', 'Holi, festival, colors, light', 'Slide194.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(195, 'Tiger Dance', 'The Puli Kali or Tiger Dance is a type of dance from Kerala. Trained artists dress up as tigers to entertain people during Onam festival.', 'The theme of the Onam festival is tiger hunting, thus, the dance.', 'occational', 'boy', 'Kerala', 'tiger, costume', 'Slide195.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(196, 'Malavath Poorna', 'Malavath Poorna  is an Indian mountaineer. On 25 May 2014, Poorna scaled the highest peak of Mount Everest and, aged 13 years and 11 months, became the youngest Indian and the youngest girl in the world to have reached the summit. ', 'A movie based on her life story was released in 2017 named Poorna: Courage Has No Limit directed by Rahul Bose.', 'Proffesion', 'girl', 'All', 'mountain, mountaineer, summit', 'Slide196.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', 'book1'),
(197, 'Pula JaDa', 'Pula Jada is a braid decorated with flowers. It is mostly used by brides in Indian marriages. It is a traditional bridal hairstyle in South Indian weddings. Roses and jasmine flowers are the most prominent flowers used as they are fragrant and available in abundance in the region. ', 'Not only are the flowers fragrant and aesthetically pleasing, they are also considered auspicious and add to the thee of weddings.', 'occasional', 'girl', 'Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Kerala, Karnataka', 'wedding, hairstyle, braid, flowers', 'Slide197.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(198, 'Pothuraju', 'Pothuraju is another avatar of Vishnu. He is considered a guardian angel in parts of India. Pothurajus are priests who worship Lord Pothuraju. He is known as Potraj in the other states of India. ', 'The Potrajus are a vanishing tribe that come from  Maharashtra.', 'Religious', 'boy', 'Maharastra', 'vishnu, pothuraju, guardian angels', 'Slide198.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(199, 'Yoga Woman', 'When doing yoga, women wear loose pants and loose shirts. Yoga began as a spiritual practice but it also promotes physical and mental well-being.', 'Yoga originated from India', 'other', 'girl', 'All', 'yoga, women, loose clothing', 'Slide199.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(200, 'Yoga (Male)', 'tbd', 'tbd', 'tbd', 'boy', 'All', '', 'Slide200.PNG', 'proposed', 'Ishana', NULL),
(201, 'Christian Nun', 'Nuns wear a distinctive head covering and veil. Women  also wear long dresses like gowns that are full sleeved. Most of the fabric is solid color like black, white or a lighter color like grey. No patterns are used.', 'They dedicate their entire lives to the service of others', 'Religious', 'girl', 'all', 'Christian, Roman, white, gray, black', 'Slide201.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(202, 'Ayyappa Devotee', 'Ayyappa is a Hindu deity, mostly worshipped in Kerala. Worshippers of Ayyappa typically wear an all black outfit consisting of a plain black shirt and pants or dhoti/lungi. Only men wear this. They will also sometimes wear a yellow scarf or sandalwood paste (sindor). ', 'The famous temple dedicated to Ayyappa is in Kerala and is the called Sabarimala.', 'religious', 'boy', 'Kerala', 'sindur, ayyappa, worship, devotee', 'Slide202.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(203, 'Vishnu Temple Priest', 'Vishnu Temple Gurus tend to wear yellow or saffron(orange) colored clothes. They usually wear a dhoti and or a lungi based on where they are located. Some of them put a vertical bindi on their foreheads', 'A guru is a teacher, a counselor, a friend and many more', 'religious', 'boy', 'all', 'gurus, saffron', 'Slide203.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(204, 'Shiva Temple Priest', 'A Shiva temple priest performs rituals at a temple worshiping Lord Shiva. He dresses similar to any Hindu priest, a dhoti and cloth wrapped around the chest. This is most commonly in the white color. ', 'Shiva temple priests tend to apply a horizontal bindi on their foreheads', 'religious', 'boy', 'All', 'priest, Shiva, Lord, dhoti', 'Slide204.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(205, 'BiLLa BanTrotu (Office Clerk)', 'During British rule, many Indian workers took on the role of Office clerks or assistants. They would dress themselves in all white and wear a red cloth around their upper body to differentiate themselves from other workers. ', 'The role of the clerk is slowly diminishing.', 'Profession', 'boy', 'all', 'hats, turban, work, white', 'Slide205.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(206, 'Mumtaz Kazi', 'Mumtaz M. Kazi is an Indian train engineer who is also regarded as the first Indian woman to drive a diesel engine train. She is also Asia\'s first woman locomotive driver. She was awarded the prestigious Nari Shakti Puraskar in March 2017 coinciding the International Women\'s Day from the then Indian President Pranab Mukherjee.', 'A hijab is a veil (head covering) worn by some Muslim women.', '', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'muslim, hijab, first', 'Slide206.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', 'book1'),
(207, 'Professional Drummer ', 'Drums are both Western as well as traditional Indian instruments.\r\n\r\nPercussion caters to Western music, while a drum called \'dhol\' is used for more Indian types of music. There are several different types of drums and they come in various shapes as well. Sometimes the harness is worn around the head and sometimes around the waist.', 'Drummers are typically male as the drums might be heavy to carry.', 'regional', 'boy', 'NA', '', 'Slide207.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'TBD,Smriti', NULL),
(208, 'Village Drummer', 'Village drummers are very common in rural areas of India. They carry a hand drum and play it during village gatherings, for dance, storytelling, or special rituals. The main outfit depends on the location of the village.', 'These drums are played for all prominent occasions in the villages.', 'Occasional', 'boy', 'All', 'drum, village, drummer', 'Slide208.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(209, 'Professional Band Member', ' Both music and dance are emblematic components of Indian weddings. Traditional live music groups will offer accompaniment to customary folk dances with old Indian wedding songs played on classical instruments like the sitar, tubla, tempura, thumba, and dohl. Professional band members at weddings will adorn a uniform with festive colors that separate them from the wedding guests. ', 'Sangeet can literally translate to the words “music” or “sung together”? This grand celebration is all about the music, embracing old and new Indian wedding songs as family and friends get to know one another .', 'Profession ', 'boy', 'all', 'hats, turban, wedding, instruments, music', 'Slide209.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(210, 'Chenda Melam Drummer', 'Chenda\'s are a very popular instrument in Kerala. They are much longer than tablas and are played with sticks. Players will wear a white dhoti/lungi and often no shirt on top. ', 'A traditional Chenda learning always starts and ends with a \"Ganapathi Kai\". This is a song worshipping lord Ganapathi.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Kerala', 'drums, instruments, kerala', 'Slide210.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(211, 'Kallu Geetha Karmikudu', 'Kallu Geetha Karmikudu are Toddy Collectors. They collect sap from different types of palm trees and make wine out of it. They wear clothes made for outdoors work and comfortable shoes.', 'Toddy is considered to be an alcoholic beverage. ', 'occupational', 'boy', 'Tamil Nadu', 'hats, turban', 'Slide211.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'smriti', NULL),
(212, 'Lord Narada', 'Lord Narada is a Vedic sage, known in Hindu tales as a musician and storyteller who carries ample wisdom with him. He wears a dhoti and carries khartal and tanpura, both musical instruments. In addition he travels barefoot and wears many malas, or garlands, around his neck, hair, and arms.', 'Lord Narada was gifted with a boon of all knowledge of the past, present, and future. But his immense knowledge became an issue for the Gods so he was cursed that nobody would ever believe him!', 'Profession, Other', 'boy', 'All', 'Narada, sage, Vedic, khartal, tanpura, mala, garland, dhoti', 'Slide212.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(213, 'Annamayya', 'Tallapaka Annamacharya (also popularly known as Annamayya) was a 15th-century Hindu saint and the earliest known Indian musician to compose songs called sankeertanas in praise of the Lord Venkateswara, a form of Vishnu a Hindu deity. He is the first known composer in carnatic music. The musical form of the keerthana songs that he composed, are still popular. ', 'Annamayya is widely regarded as the Andhra Pada kavitā Pitāmaha (Grandfather of Telugu song-writing).\r\n\r\n', 'People,author', 'boy', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'singer, Vishnu, saint, music', 'Slide213.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(214, 'Subramanya Bharathi', 'Subramanya Bharathi was a Tamilian. He wrote poems and journals during the Indian Independence movement. He wore a white turban and dark blue or black attire. ', 'He had a tremendous influence on Tamilian literature. ', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'Tamil Nadu', 'hats, turban, patriotism', 'Slide214.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(215, 'Pano Bhaju', 'Pano Bhaju is the traditional dress of Goa. This is a 9 yard saree and the designs take inspiration from the clothing of Persia, China and Central Asia. Wendell Rodricks is the one who traveled along the silk road to finally put together this design in Goa.', 'Pano Bhaju can be worn plain or with very heavy jewelry', 'regional', 'girl', 'Goa', 'saree, jewlery, traditional', 'Slide215.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(216, 'Kabuli Wala', 'Kabuli Wala is the story about a merchant who comes to India each year to sell fruits and merchandise. He is from the city of Kabul in Afghanistan. ', 'Kabuliwala has been made into many movies, especially in Bollywood.', 'Other', 'boy', 'All', 'kabul, afghanistan, dhoti, kurta, vest', 'Slide216.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(217, 'Bengali Man', 'Textile production in Bengal dates back to the 4th century BCE. They were shipped to ancient Greece and Rome! Bengali men wear kurtas (long tops), lungis (skirt like bottoms),or sarongs (a long piece of cloth wrapped around the body and tucked in at the waist. ', 'Many prominent Indians wore this outfit during the freedom struggle.', 'regional', 'boy', 'West Bengal, Bangladesh', 'kurta, lungi, sarong', 'Slide217.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(218, 'Chenchu', 'Chenchu is a very ancient tribe. While there is not much information about them around the world, they are skilled huntsman. They often wear orange attire and a green scarf around their head.', 'A lot of times they hunt deep into the night.', 'regional', 'boy', 'N/A', 'huntsman, archery, hunting', 'Slide218.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(219, 'Romani Girl', 'The Romani people are an Indo-Aryan ethnic group. The young girls wear loose shirts and long skirts. Their hair is usually kept long. Nowadays, girls may also wear loose pants.', 'The Romani are also known as Gypsies.', 'other', 'girl', 'NA', 'Skirts, loose', 'Slide219.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(220, 'Panche', 'Panche is a fancy dress worn by males in the Panchala function. The dress consists of a dhoti, kurta, and shawl-like wrap. The material and design is very fancy, and even a necklace or other accessories are worn.', 'This function is when a boy wears a dhoti for the first time.', 'Occasion', 'boy', 'All', 'panche, panchala, dhoti', 'Slide220.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(221, 'Patiala Suit', 'A Patiala salwar is a type of female trousers which has its roots in Patiala City in the Northern region of Punjab .The Patiala trousers are preferred by most of the women of Punjab and other regions of Northern India for comfort and durability in summers. Since the Patiala salwar is very loose and stitched with pleats it is a very comfortable outfit to wear. Its distinguishing characteristic is folds of cloth stitched together that meet at the bottom.', 'The King of Patiala in earlier times wore a Patiala salwar as his royal dress.', 'regional', 'boy', 'ALL, Rajasthan, Gujarat, Haryana, Punjab', 'comfort, trousers, pleated', 'Slide221.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(222, 'Gattu', 'Gattu is a mascot created by cartoonist R.K. Laxman for a then-small company called Asian Paints. It was born in a garage in the 1940s before it was big. The mascot was made in 1954. ', 'Gattu is portrayed as very mischievous.', 'people', 'boy', 'N/A', 'gattu, mascot, painting', 'Slide222.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(223, 'Farshi Pajama', 'The Farshi Pajama is a womens dress that was worn in Muslim courts by royalty and in the privileged classes of Uttar Pradesh. This dress has loose pants that look like a skirt and a long dress.', 'Farsi comes from the Iranian language, and this outfit is worn in many countries.', ' regional', 'girl', 'Uttar Pradesh.', 'pants, loose, dress, skirt', 'Slide223.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(224, 'Cricketer (Male)', 'The male cricketer uniform is very similar to the female cricketer uniform. It contains the full or half sleeves shirt and long pants. In addition, shin guards and sturdy running shoes. During certain parts of the cricket game, a much sturdier helmet is worn. The Indian cricket color is blue, so the entire uniform is in that color. ', 'Some Indian cricketers include Sachin Tendulkar, Virak Kohli, and MS Dhoni. These players are not only known for being the best in India, but also worldwide.', 'Profession', 'boy', 'All', 'Cricket, Shin Guards, Helmet, Blue', 'Slide224.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(225, 'Dilja Design', 'Dilja Design was a popular type of women\'s attire during the Mughal Empire. Mughal clothing was developed in the 16th, 17th and 18th centuries throughout the extent of their empire in the Indian subcontinent. It was characterized by luxurious styles and was made with muslin, silk, velvet and brocade.  Women wore much jewelry including earrings, nose jewelry, necklaces, bangles, belts, and anklets.\r\n', 'Elaborate patterns including dots, checks, and waves were used with colors from various dyes including cochineal, sulfate of iron, sulfate of copper and sulfate of antimony were used.\r\n\r\n', 'Historical', 'girl', 'all', 'jewelry, Mughal Empire, velvet, dyes, silk', 'Slide225.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(226, 'Bhishi Water Carrier', 'Bhishi\'s carry water from the oceans/rivers back to houses to boil the water so that it can be drinkable. They will wear simple attire that is light and airy because of the heat and their strenuous work. ', 'They can carry several pounds of water on their long trips.', 'regional', 'boy', 'N/A', 'water, carrier', 'Slide226.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(227, 'Baiga Tribe (Woman)', 'The Baiga are an ethnic group. They often decorate themselves in colorful manners using elements and materials from the forests they live in.', 'Baiga people consider themselves as the heirs of the earth.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Madhya Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh and Jharkhand', 'hats, turban', 'Slide227.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(228, 'Baiga Tribe (Man)', 'The Baiga tribe is an ethnic group located in several states across India. They are considered to be very poor, and wear minimal clothing from materials they find in the forest region where they live.', 'The Baiga tribe does not plow land, as they believe that is scratching the mother earth.', 'regional, tribal', 'boy', 'Madhya Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh,\nJharkhand', 'baiga, poor, forest', 'Slide228.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(229, 'dongria kondh woman', 'The Dongria Kondh people are members of the Kondhs. They are located in the Niyamgiri hills in the state of Odisha (formerly Orissa) in India. They sustain themselves from the resources of the Niyamgiri forests, practicing horticulture and shifting cultivation. The Dongria have distinctive jewelry, tattoos and hairstyles. Women wear many rings through their ears and three through their noses. Dongria girls wear clips in their hair and rings and beads around their necks. ', 'They derive their name from dongar, meaning ‘hill’ and the name for themselves is Jharnia: protector of streams.', 'regional, tribal', 'girl', 'Odisha', 'tribal, jewelry, hills, rings, beads, clips', 'Slide229.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(230, 'Dongria Kondh man', 'Dongria men gather juice from the forest’s sago palm trees, a drink that provides energy for the long hikes they make through the Niyamgiri Hills.', 'Boys will wear 2 nose rings while women wear 3. ', 'regional', 'boy', 'Odisha', 'dongria, men, carriers', 'Slide230.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(231, 'Kotagarh Pahari Woman', 'The Pahari people are an Indo-Aryan ethnic group of the Himalayas living in the Himalayan regions of India. The women wear simple clothes that keep them warm but allow them to be very mobile.', 'The Pahari are an agricultural people.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'simple, skirt, dress', 'Slide231.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(232, 'Lepcha Woman*', 'The Lepchas are an indigenous people of Sikkim (North eastern state in India) and Nepal. Most Lepchas are Buddhist. \r\nThe traditional clothing for Lepcha women is the ankle-length dumvun, also called dumdyám or gādā (\"female dress\"). It is one large piece of smooth cotton or silk, usually of a solid color. When it is worn, it is folded over one shoulder, pinned at the other shoulder, and held in place by a waistband, or tago, over which excess material drapes. A contrasting long-sleeved blouse may be worn underneath.\r\n\r\nThe traditional Lepcha clothing for men is the thakraw (\"male dress\"). It is a multicolored, hand-woven cloth pinned at one shoulder and held in place by a waistband, usually worn over white shirt and trousers. Men wear a flat round cap called a thyáktuk, with stiff black velvet sides and a multicolored top topped by a knot. Rarely, the traditional cone-shaped bamboo and rattan hats are worn.', 'The Lepchas are mostly agriculturists. They grow oranges, rice, cardamoms, and other foods', 'regional, tribal', 'girl', 'North India', 'lepcha, dumbun', 'Slide232.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(233, 'Khasi Man', 'The Khasi people are an indigenous ethnic group of Meghalaya in north-eastern India. The traditional male dress is a jymphong, a long sleeveless coat without a collar. They also wear ornamental waist-bands and turbans. Nowadays, most male Khasis have adapted western attire but appear in a jymphong for ceremonial occasions. ', 'A cultural tradition of Khasis is to follow the matrilineal system of decent and inheritance.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Meghalaya', 'hats, turban, tribes, waist-band', 'Slide233.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha ', NULL),
(234, 'Air Hostess', 'Air India is India\'s largest airline company. The air hostesses who work for this company will typically wear saris, but they might also wear a skirt and shirt like other country\'s hostesses. These women have a lot of work to do while in the air. ', 'Indian air hostesses will speak both English and Hindi on the flight to passengers. ', 'people', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'Dress, Formal ', 'Slide234.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(235, 'Nurse', 'Nurses wear scrubs while working. These scrubs include a jacket over a shirt and a skirt or pants. Some women choose to wear a saree and a jacket over that.', 'Nurses also go through a rigorous training and academics. In some rural areas, the expertise of nurses is sought owing to lack of doctors.', 'occupational', 'girl', 'All', 'simple, skirt, pants, saree', 'Slide235.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(236, 'Vajpayee', 'Atal Bihari Vajpayee was a former prime minister of India. He was known to always wear a white color dhoti and kurta with a (blue) solid colored vest on top. Vajpayee served three terms as Indian prime minister!', 'He was known to be an excellent orator.', 'Profession,author', 'boy', 'All', 'prime minister, dhoti, kurta, vest, patriotism', 'Slide236.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(237, 'PV Narasimharao', 'Pamulaparthi Venkata Narasimha Rao was an Indian lawyer and politician who served as the 9th Prime Minister of India from 1991 to 1996. He led an important administration, overseeing a major economic transformation and several home incidents affecting national security of India. He often wore a dhoti and achkan (knee length jacket) or kurta.', 'Rao was able to speak 17 languages Telugu, Marathi, Hindi, Oriya, Bengali, Gujarati, Kannada, Sanskrit, Tamil  Urdu, English, French, Arabic, Spanish, German and Persian.', 'people,author', 'boy', 'Telangana', 'kurta, politician, prime minister, patriotism', 'Slide237.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(238, 'Gabbar Singh', 'Gabbar Singh is a fictional movie character. He plays a iconic villain. He wears a dark blue shirt and matching pants. He often holds a gun with him.', ' He is in the movie Sholay. ', 'regional, people', 'boy', 'Manipur', 'singh, villain, movies', 'Slide238.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(239, 'Bell Bottom Pants (Man)', 'Bell Bottom pants are very famous for being a style from the 70s. These pants are regular fit from the waist to the shins and once they reach your mid shin, they flare out. This was a popular style in Bollywood movies at the time.', 'Carlo Casini is known as the creator of Bell Bottoms', 'other', 'boy', 'NA', 'pants, bollywood, 70s', 'Slide239.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(240, 'Bell Bottom Pants (Woman)', 'Bell bottom pants were tight fitting pants up until the knees, then flared until the ankles. This style was popular in the 1970s, and many Bollywood actresses sported this look with a top and scarf.', 'These pants now come in many different styles, designs, colors, and fabrics!', 'Other', 'girl', 'All', 'bell bottom pants, flare, 1970', 'Slide240.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(241, 'Telugu Gabbar Singh (Fancy Dress)', 'Gabbar Singh is a fictional character and was originally the antagonist of the 1975 film Sholay. The character was later used in the Telugu film Gabbar Singh in which he became the protagonist and was remembered as a heroic figure. In the Telugu rendition, Gabbar Singh would wear unbuttoned cargo shirts with police logos and tie a red cloth around his head before fighting. He also wore black sunglasses and occasionally hooded shirts.  ', 'Gabbar Singh has a sequel and both movies use dialogues from the original 1975 movie!', 'Fancy dress', 'boy', 'South India', 'movie, hero, police, red, cargo shirt', 'Slide241.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(242, 'Mysore Peta', 'Mysore Peta is the classical royal Indian attire worn by the Kings of Mysuru. They wore bejeweled turbans made of silk to match with colorful dresses as part of the royal dress.', 'The traditional Mysuru peta has been retained as a symbol of heritage', 'regional', 'boy', 'Mysore', 'hats, turbans', 'Slide242.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(243, 'Mithila Paag', 'The Paag is a type of headdress. It is a symbol of honor and respect in the Mithila culture. The Paag dates back to pre-historic times when it was made of plant leaves. It exists today in a modified form.', ' The Mithila Paag was once featured on a postage stamp.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Bihar and Jharkhand', 'hats, turbans', 'Slide243.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(244, 'Angami Tribal Cap', 'The Angami tribal cap is worn by Angami men, in the state of Nagaland. It is a very large cap, with a part that goes around the head, then the rest sticking outward from there.', 'The Angami people are one of the only groups from Nagaland who practice wet-rice cultivation, which allows them to use the same land each year.', 'regional, tribal', 'boy', 'Nagalad', 'angami, hat, cap', 'Slide244.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(245, 'Dastar  (Sikh Turban)', 'A Dastar is a Sikh turban and an article of faith that represents honor, self respect, courage, spirituality, and piety. The Sikhs regard the Dastar as an important part of their unique identity. ', 'The term Dastar is Persian and can refer to any type of turban, not just the Sikh headwear!', ' religious', 'boy', 'all', 'hats, turbans, sikh, headwear', 'Slide245.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(246, 'Tepi (or “Brokpa” or “Drokpa” Tribe)', 'The Brokpa are a small community of people who live in the Kashmir region. The head dress is very large and extravagant, but is extraordinary to look at. ', 'They are a fast vanishing tribe.', 'regional', 'girl', 'Kashmir', 'hats, tepi, tribes', 'Slide246.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(247, 'Tepi (or “Brokpa” or “Drokpa” Tribe)', 'The Brokpa are a small community of Dard people who live in the Jammu and Kashmir region. The Tepi, headdress, is very floral and extravagant.', 'The Brokpa people are trying very hard to preserve their culrture.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Jammu and Kashmir ', 'hats, turbans', 'Slide247.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Smriti', NULL),
(248, 'Japi or Jaapi Cap', 'The Japi cap is an extremely large cap from the state of Assam. It is made from tightly woven bamboo, and palm leaves.', 'Plain Japi caps are worn by farmers in Assam for sun protection. Fancier and more ornate Japi caps are worn by royalty as a symbol of status.', 'regional', 'boy', 'Assam', 'hats, turbans, cap, bamboo, palm leaves', 'Slide248.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ishana', NULL),
(249, 'Hornbill Warrior Cap', 'The Hornbill is a very rare bird and is the State bird of the Indian state of Nagaland. A set of 16 stamps was issued by India Post on Headgears of India on Feb 10, 2017. These headgears from different parts of the country signify social ,cultural and community values. \n\n', 'The number of hornbill feathers used on the traditional Headgear in Nagaland is like medals of achievement. ', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Nagaland', 'hats, turbans, stamp, feathers', 'Slide249.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Nikhitha', NULL),
(250, 'Bison Horn Maria Tribe', 'Out of the nearly billion people that live in India, the Bison Horn Maria Tribe consist of about 9,500 people. They wear very colorful outfits with red being the majority color. Women will wear many necklaces while men wear a hat that has bison horns on it. ', 'The caps were made from horns of now-extinct bison. ', 'regional, people', 'boy', 'Madhya Pradesh, Maharashtra', 'bison horn, tribes, hats', 'Slide250.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ria', NULL),
(251, 'Budugu', 'Budugu is a fictional character created by Mullapudi Venkata Ramana. The drawings of Budugu are by Bapu, a very famous artist. The character wears a green dhoti with a tan shirt.\r\n\r\nBudugu is a precocious and bratty child, characterized by his inimitably childish Telugu. Mullapudi describes the world as seen through his eyes', 'Budugu was the childhood nickname of Ramana. ', 'Regional, Book_Character', 'boy', 'AP, TS', 'Fancy Dress, dhoti, fictional', 'Slide251.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ahala', NULL),
(252, 'Seegana pesunamba', 'Seegana is the childhood crush of Budugu. The book is a fictional creation of Mullapudi Venkata Ramana, and is considered to be one of the most widely read childhood books.  \r\n\r\n\r\nFrom Telugu states;', 'Seegana pesunamba is a girl a year younger than Budugu and often teases him.', 'Regional,Book_Character', 'girl', 'AP, TS', 'Fancy Dress', 'Slide252.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ahala', NULL),
(253, 'KCR Dress', 'Kalvakuntla Chandrashekhar Rao is a political leader and the 1st Chief Minister of Telangana, serving since 2014. He is the leader and founder of the Telangana Rashtra Samithi, a regional party in Telangana, India. He is known for leading the Telangana movement to achieve statehood for Telangana.', 'KCR is known to popularly wear Khadi clothes from Pondur in Srikakulam.', 'sample', 'boy', 'TS', 'Fancy Dress', 'Slide253.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(254, 'Venkaiah Naidu Dress', 'Muppavarapu Venkaiah Naidu (born 1 July 1949) is an Indian politician. He was an ex-Vice President of India and the Chairman of the Rajya Sabha. Previously, he served as the Minister of Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation, Urban Development and Information and Broadcasting in the Modi Cabinet.', ' He first gained attention for his prominent role in the Jai Andhra Movement of 1972.', 'Regional', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide254.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(255, 'MGR Dress', 'Maruthur Gopala Menon Ramachandran (1917 - 1987), otherwise known as MGR, was an Indian Politician and film actor. He served as the Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu between 1977 and 1987 and founded the AIADMK, a political party. Ramachandran made his film debut in 1936, in the film Sathi Leelavathi.', 'His last film was Ullagam Suthi Paru, in which he acted even though he knew he was diagnosed with kidney failure. He said that there was no question in ‘retirement for anyone anywhere in the cine field.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Regional', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide255.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(256, 'NTR Dress (Turban)', 'Nandamuri Taraka Rama Rao, known as NTR, is an Indian Politician and Film Actor. He has won many awards such as three National Film Awards for co-producing and directing movies. NTR founded the Telugu Desam Party (TDP) on March 29th, 1982.\r\nHe was one of the most prolific actors of his time. The roles he played to showcase Lord Krishna made him immensely popular. Along with ANR, NTR was the other pillar of Telugu Film industry.', 'NTR served as Chief Minister of Andhra Pradesh for 7 years over 3 terms.', 'Regional', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide256.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(257, 'Gujarati Pagidi', 'The pagidi is a head piece that is worn for both daily as well as occasional purposes. The type of pagidi determines the occasion. For example, a pagidi with a long flair is worn for festivals and weddings. For Diwali and Garba, people wear colorful pagidis.', 'A Pagdi can be worn by both men and women, but is typically worn by men.', 'Regional', 'boy', '', 'turbans, pagidi, hats', 'Slide257.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(258, 'Rajasthan Pagidi', 'A Rajashthani pagidi is a very colorful head piece that is typically worn by men. The pagidi is generally made of cotton and he also used to keep cool during the extremely hot weather in Rajasthan.', 'An unraveled turban can also be used as a rope to draw water from a well with a bucket.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Regional', 'boy', '', 'turbans, pagidi, hats', 'Slide258.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(259, 'Haryanvi Pagdi (Haryana)', 'A Hariyanvi Pagri is a turban or headgear for men. It is a rolled piece of a long cloth wrapped around the head. Although now fully stitched pagris are available which are required to be worn as simple as a hat.', 'In recent times, Pagris are only seen on older men.', 'Regional', 'boy', 'Haryana', 'turbans, pagidi, hats', 'Slide259.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(260, 'Sri Shirdi Sai Baba', 'Sai Baba was an early 20th century spiritual saint. He was revered by Hindus and Muslims alike. His teachings encouraged tolerance and kindness towards all. He spoke strongly against discriminating between religions.  He is known to have performed several miracles to help his devotees. The exact whereabouts of his birth (time, location, and parents) are unknown.', 'A temple dedicated to Sai Baba is located in Shirdi, in the state of Maharashtra. Millions of devotees visit the temple every year to pay homage.', 'Religious', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide260.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(261, 'Ballad (folk) Singer', 'TBD', 'TBD', 'regional', 'boy', 'AP, Telangana', '', 'Slide261.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(262, 'Nazar', 'Burra Katha', 'Burra Katha', 'regional', 'boy', 'AP,  TN', '', 'Slide262.PNG', 'proposed', 'Bookmark', 'book1'),
(263, 'Kavvali Singer', 'Kavvali or Qawali is a form of Sufi Islamic devotional music. It is popular mainly in the Asian subcontinent regions including Pakistan, Northern India, and Bangladesh. ', 'Several Qawai songs were made popular in Bollywood. Nustral Fateh Ali Khan was a very famous Qawali singer.', 'other', 'boy', 'all', '', 'Slide263.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(264, 'Gangireddu', 'Gangireddu people are from nomadic castes from the Andhra-Karnataka region who receive old oxen from farmers after the oxen become unfit for farming. The Gangireddu walk from door to door begging for old used clothes, and they blow trumpets to entertain the people whose house they visit. In Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, they visit houses where people would come out to offer food to the ox and take blessings as the oxen and cattle as a whole are regarded as holy.', 'They are most popular during the Sankranthi season.', 'festivals', 'boy', 'AP, TN', '', 'Slide264.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(265, 'Hari Katha', 'Harikatha is a form of Hindu storytelling in which the singer explores a traditional theme, often from the life of an Indian epic. The person telling the story through songs, music, and narration is called a Haridasa.', 'Usually, the narration involves numerous sub-plots and anecdotes, which are used to emphasize various aspects of the main story.', 'people', 'girl', 'TBD', '', 'Slide265.PNG', 'proposed', 'ToDO ', 'book1'),
(266, 'Hari Katha Artist ', 'Harikatha is a form of Hindu storytelling in which the singer explores a traditional theme, often from the life of an Indian epic. The person telling the story through songs, music, and narration is called a Haridasa.', 'Usually, the narration involves numerous sub-plots and anecdotes, which are used to emphasize various aspects of the main story.\n\n\n', 'people', 'boy', 'tbd', 'tbd', 'Slide266.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(267, 'Fisherman', 'Fishermen engage in activities related to catching fish and other sea food, with the intention of selling them to customers and thus making a living. In the olden days, fishing was done with primitive methods including laying fishing nets etc. However nowadays fishing is done with complete machinery and advanced methods', 'In India, the coastal states in South India are abound with fisheries.', 'people', 'boy', 'all', '', 'Slide267.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(268, 'Parrot (Tarot) Card Reader', 'Parrot Astrology is a type of astrology that is most popular in Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, and Singapore. Green parakeets are trained to pick from tarot cards, and the card is believed to show your fate. Once the parakeet picks a card from the 27 cards that are laid down in a specific order, the astrologer then opens the card and interprets the image to tell the patron their fate.', 'The practice of Parrot astrology is diminishing in Tamil Nadu due to lack of patronage.', 'people', 'boy', 'All', '', 'Slide268.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(269, 'Snake Charmer', 'Snake charming is the art of appearing to hypnotize a snake by waving and playing an instrument called a pungi. This act might include making the snake do dangerous acts, and it is also often performed on the sides of streets. These charmers usually all have the same dressing, whether they are in India or Pakistan; long hair, a turban, earrings, and necklaces made up of shells.', 'The earliest proof of snake charming comes from ancient Egyptian sources.', 'people', 'boy', 'All', '', 'Slide269.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(270, 'TappeTa guLLu Artist', 'Tappeta Gullu is a folk dance of Andhra Pradesh. It is very popular in theaters, folk dances, ballads, and dance drama. Tappeta is known as a ritualistic performance. The dancers perform many acrobatic moves as well.', 'A group of roughly 15-20 men perform the dance at one time. They wear ghungroo (bells) on their feet.', 'regional', 'boy', 'AP, TS', '', 'Slide270.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(271, 'Train Conductor (Boy)', 'A train conductor is a part of the train crew that is in charge of safety duties that do not involve the actual train/locomotive. The conductor title is mostly used in North America, but the role is common worldwide.', 'The Indian Railways is among the largest employers in India. ', 'people', 'boy', 'India', 'Professions', 'Slide271.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(272, 'Train Conductor (Girl)', 'A train conductor is a part of the train crew that is in charge of safety duties that do not involve the actual train/locomotive. The conductor title is mostly used in North America, but the role is common worldwide.', 'Indian Railways: One of the top 10 largest employers in the world.', 'People', 'girl', 'India', 'Profession', 'Slide272.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(273, 'Dr. Babu Rajendra Prasad', 'Rajendra Prasad was born in the Siwan district of Bihar. He was a lawyer, scholar, Indian Independence activist, and the first President of India. He served in office from 1950 to 1962. He joined the Indian National Congress during the Indian Independence Movement and became a leader from the region of Bihar. ', 'Rajendra Prasad was the first President of Independent India', 'people', 'boy', 'Bihar', 'Leaders, patriotism', 'Slide273.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(274, 'Gurkha (Night Watchman)', 'Gurkha Regiment', 'Gurkha Regiment', 'people', 'boy', 'India', '', 'Slide274.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(275, 'Sarojini Naidu', 'Sarojini Naidu was an important figure in India’s independence struggle. Her work as a renowned poetess earned her the title of “Nightingale of India”. Sarojini Naidu was born in current day Hyderabad to Bengali parents. She was closely associated with Mahatma Gandhi during the British rule. She was one of the first female Presidents of the Indian National Congress.', 'Mrs. Naidu has an asteroid named in her honor. ', 'people,author', 'girl', '', 'Leaders, patriotism', 'Slide275.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', 'book1'),
(276, 'MahanaTi Savithri', 'Savitri Ganesan, born Nissankara Savitri, was an Indian actress, singer, dancer, producer, and director who was primarily known for her work in the Telugu and Tamil film industries, although she had also worked in Kannada, Malayalam, and Hindi films. She is known as the first female superstar in the South Indian film industry and has starred in more than 250 films in 3 decades, and her debut film was Pelli Chesi Choodu in 1952, which was simultaneously shot in Telugu and Tamil. She is often regarded as ‘Mahanati’ or ‘Nadigaiyar Thilagam’.', 'In 2018, a biopic about Savitri was shot starring Keerthy Suresh. It became the highest-grossing South Indian film that starred a woman as the main character.', 'people', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide276.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', 'book1'),
(277, 'ChiTTi - The Robot', 'Shivaji Rao Gaekwad, well-known as Rajinikanth, is an Indian actor who primarily works in Tamil cinema. He is also a screenwriter and producer. He’s won many awards, such as the Filmfare Best Tamil Actor Award and 4 Tamil Nadu State Film Best Actor Awards. He has even been awarded a Padma Bhushan by the Government of India. He debuted in the film Apoorva Raagangal in 1975. In Ethiran, or in Telugu, Robo, Rajinikanth plays dual roles as a scientist and an andro humanoid robot, whose name is Chitti. This film also has a 2018 sequel, 2.0.', 'Ethiran and 2.0 were both India’s most expensive productions at the time of their release and among one of the highest-grossing Indian films of all time.', 'people', 'boy', 'Tamil Nadu', '', 'Slide277.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(278, 'Jyothirao Phule', 'Jyothirao Govindrao Phule was an Indian social activist, anti-caste social reformer, and writer from Maharashtra. He also made efforts in educating women. He and his wife, Savitribai Phule, were pioneers of women’s education in India.', 'Phule was bestowed with the honorific Mahatma title by Maharashtrian social activist Vithalrao Krishnaji Vandekar in 1888.', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'Maharashtra', '', 'Slide278.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(279, 'Koya Dora', 'Koya Dora is a tribal community that is predominant found in the states of Telangana, Andhra, and Odisha. They speak the Koya language. ', 'They have an important role to play in the Medaram jatara in Telanga every year.', 'regional', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide279.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(280, 'GussaDi Man', 'The Gusadi Dance is popular in the Gond community. Deepavali is the biggest festival for the Raj Gonds of Adilabad district in Telangana State. Gonds dress in colourful costumes and are decorated with ornaments. They go to neighboring villages in troupes, singing and dancing. Such troupes are called Dandari dance troupes. This starts on the full moon day and goes on till the fourteenth day of the dark fortnight of Deepavali.', 'Kanaka Raju from Komaram Bheem district was awarded the Padma Shri due to his dedication in the past 60 years to GussaDi dance.', 'regional', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide280.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(281, 'Chiranjeevi - Sankardada 2', 'Chiranjeevi, born as Konidela Siva Sankara Vara Prasad, is an Indian actor and former politician. His acting career has lasted 39 years (and counting), and has won awards such as 3 Andhra Pradesh State Nandi Awards, 9 Filmfare Awards South, a Ragupathi Venkaiah Award, and was even awarded a Padma Bhushan in 2006. He began his career in 1978 with the film Punadhirallu. ', 'He won the Filmfare Award for Best Actor for the film Shankar Dada M.B.B.S, which also had a sequel named Shankar Dada Zindabaad.', 'movies', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide281.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(282, 'Lord Murugan', 'Lord Murugan is an important Hindu god, worshipped in Southern India. He is the son of Lord Shiva and Goddess Parvati. He was the commander-in-chief of the celestial army. He was born to slay the evil demon Tarakasura. To his devotees, Lord Murugan symbolizes youth, beauty, valor and wisdom. He has two wives – Devasena and Valli.', 'Lord Murugan’s younger brother is the popular elephant faced God - Ganesha. Murugan is also known as Skanda, Mahasena or Karttikeya in different parts of India.', 'religious', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide282.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ahala', NULL),
(283, 'Sri Krishna Devaraya', 'Sri Krishna Devaraya was a ruler of the Vijayanagara empire, in current day South India. He had a keen eye for the arts and encouaraged many poets and artists during his reign. Krishna Devaraya was a renowned poet himself. Under his rule, the Vijayanagara empire grew to great prosperity. Its capital Hampi is now a UNESCO world heritage site.', 'There were eight poets at Sri Krishna Devaraya’s court called the Ashtadiggajas (Ashta represents eight in Sanskrit). These eight were stalwarts in their chosen fields of poetry, literature, and intellect.', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide283.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ahala', NULL),
(284, 'Duryodhana', 'Mahabharat, a great Indian epic is the story of the Pandava and the Kauravas. Duryodhana was the oldest of the Kauravas. He had ninety-nine brothers and one sister. His mother was Gandhari and father was Dhritarashtra, the king of Hastinapura.  Duryodhana was a valiant warrior, but unjust and arrogant too. His inability to share the kingdom with his Pandava cousins led to the Kurukshetra war.', 'Duryodhana had a skill through which allowed him to stay underwater for long hours without the need to come up for air.', '', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide284.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ahala', NULL),
(285, 'toTa Ramudu', 'Nandamuri Taraka Rama Rao, known professionally as NTR, was an Indian actor, producer, director, film editor, and politician. He debuted in the film industry with the movie Mana Desam in 1949. He gained more popularity after portraying Hindu deities, such as Rama and Krishna, which is one of the many things he is known for today. He starred in such films as Patala Bhairavi, an Indian fantasy film in which NTR portrays ‘Thota’ Rammudu. ', 'Pathala Bhairavi’s story is regularly staged as a play by the Surabi Theater Group, and the film is considered to be a breakthrough for Rama Rao.', 'dresses', 'boy', 'AP', '', 'Slide285.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(286, 'Bobbili Puli', 'Bobbili Puli is a film about a war hero who returns home to find the society he left behind in disorder, and while attempting to fix everything, he ends up putting his life at risk. The film stars NTR, a well-renowned Indian actor primarily known for his Telugu and Tamil films. ', ' The film collected around 72 lakhs in its first week, and 3.5 crores overall.', 'dresses', 'boy', 'AP', '', 'Slide286.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(287, 'Nepala MantrikuDu', 'Samarla Venkata Ranga Rao, popularly known as SVR, was an Indian actor, producer, and film director known for his work in the Telugu and Tamil industries. He was popularly known as “Viswa Nata Chakravarthi” and had a film career of 3 decades. In 1951, SVR gained popularity for his portrayal of Nepala Manthrikudu the tantric in the film Pathala Bhairavi. ', 'SVR was known for portraying mythological characters such as Ghatotkacha in the blockbuster film Maya Bazaar. This film is known to be the “greatest Indian film of all time.”', 'dresses', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide287.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(288, 'GhaTOkcuDu', 'GhaTOtkaca was the son of the Pandava prince Bheema and Hidimbi, a demoness by birth. As a result of his maternal demon heritage, GhaTOtkaca knew all kinds of magic and demon tricks. For example, he could fly. He played a crucial role in the Mahabharat war, where he sided with his father’s side, the Pandavas. A fictional story of GhaTOtkaca is in the form of a popular Telugu movie Mayabazaar.', 'GhaTOtkaca is a popular pop figure in Indonesia including Java and Bali.', 'dresses', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide288.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Ahala', NULL),
(289, 'Goutami Putra Satakarni', 'Gautamiputra Satakarni was a ruler of the Satavahana Empire in what is now the present-day Deccan region of India. He ruled in the 1st or 2nd century CE, although the exact period is uncertain.', 'In 2017, a movie based on the life of Gautamiputra was released. It starred Balakrishna in the lead role. The film was nominated for a Filmfare Award for Best Film in 2018, however, it did not win.', 'people', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide289.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(290, 'TaMguTUri Prakasham PaMtulu', 'ex-Chief Minister of Andhra Pradesh\r\n\r\n', 'tbd', 'people,\nauthor', 'boy', 'AP', 'patriotism', 'Slide290.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(291, 'kolaTam boy', 'Kolattam or Kolannalu is known as the ‘stick dance’. It is a combination of rhythmic movements and music. The Kolattam group comprises dancers ranging from 8-40 and the dancers are grouped in pairs. The sticks provide the rhythm for the dancing.', 'Kolattam is one of the most popular dance narratives in Andhra Pradesh. ', 'tbd', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide291.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(292, 'kolaTam girl', 'Kolattam or Kolannalu is known as the ‘stick dance’. It is a combination of rhythmic movements and music. The Kolattam group comprises dancers ranging from 8-40 and the dancers are grouped in pairs. The sticks provide the rhythm for the dancing.', 'Kolattam is one of the most popular dance narratives in Andhra Pradesh. ', 'tbd', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide292.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(293, 'chekka bhajana boy', 'Chekka Bhajana is a dance from. It is usually used to sing songs praising Lord Rama, and the performance itself  is called “Rama Bhajana” while the dancers are called “Rama Dandu.” In the past, each village would train a group (dandu) or dancers who would move with a lamp and an idol of Lord Rama from one village to another. ', 'The name “Chekka Bhajana” derives from the telugu word “Chekka” which means wood. This is because wooden pieces are specifically crafted into a percussion instrument which is used to accompany the music in Chekka Bhajana.', 'tbd', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide293.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(294, 'karra samu - boy', 'Karra Samu, or Kathi Samu, is a form of ancient martial art that originated in Andhra Pradesh. Kathi Samu is performed using swords, and “Kathi” means sword in Telugu. It is believed that this martial art form has been around for over 7000 years even before the Aryan dynasty came to India. ', 'Karra Samu was practiced by Royal Kings to use in wars against their enemies. It was also a matter of pride to leaven Kathi Samu.', 'tbd', 'boy', '', '', 'Slide294.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
(295, 'karra samu - girl', 'tbd', 'tbd', 'tbd', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide295.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL);
