(353, 'British-era Police', 'British-era police, more known as the Imperial Police, was part of the Indian Police Services, which was the uniform system of police administration during the British Raj. The Imperial Police system was motivated because of the 1857 rebellion and the dangers the British experienced from it.', '', NULL, 'boy', NULL, NULL, 'Slide353.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Happy', NULL),
