(506, 'Lady Meherbai Tata ', 'Lady Meherbai Tata was an Indian tennis player and wife of Sir Dorabji Tata. She was born in Bombay on October 10th, 1879. She had a strong will from a young age and refused to Westernize and change her name from \'Mehri\' to \'Mary\' even at a young age. She married Sir Dorabji Tata in 1898 and found many common interests in various topics including sports. Lady Tata also won the \'Triple Crown\' in the Western Indian Tennis Tournament. She is known for playing tennis with a saree and was also a good horse rider and pianist. She campaigned for education rights for women, banning of purdah, and the abolishment of untouchability. Suffering from leukemia, she died while being nursed in Northern Wales.', 'Lady Tata is known for selling her precious 245.35 carat diamond when the Tata steel went into financial troubles.', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide506.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
