(544, 'Nidumolu Sumathi', 'Nidumolu Sumathi is an Indian percussionist, who primarily plays the mridangam. She is regarded as one of the first female mridungam players in India and also the first female Laya Vinyasam artist. She was born in Eluru, Andhra Pradesh on 16 October, 1950. Her father was a Mridangam Vidwan and she started learning under him at the age of six. In 2003, she became an \'A-Top\' grade artist of All India Radio. She accompanied and performed with many artists including M.S. Subbalakshmi, Chittoor Subramiam Pillai, Dr. M Balamurali Krishna and U. Srinivas among others. In 2021, she was awarded with the Padma Shri for her talent in Mridungam.', 'She has been given many honorary titles including Srimukha Mridanga Vidwanmani, Mridanga Maharani, Mridanga Vinyasa Kalabharati and many others.', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide544.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
