(581, 'karanam malleswari', 'Karnam Malleswari is a retired female Indian weightlifter. She was born on June 1st, 1975 in Srikakulam, Andhra Pradesh. In 1994 Malleswari won the silver at the World Championships in Istanbul and in 1995 she won the Asian Weightlifting Championships in Korea. She has won many national championships and over 29 international medals. At the 2000 Syndeny Olympics, she secured the bronze medal which made her the first male or female Indian to win an Olympic Medal in weightlifting. Currently, she lives with her family in Yamunanagar.', 'She was awarded with the Arjuna Award and Khel Ratna Award by the Government of India.', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide581.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(582, 'koneru hampi', 'Koneru Humpy is an Indian chess player who is well known for becoming the youngest Grandmaster at 15 years, 1 month, and 27 days. She also won the FIDE Woman\'s Rapid Chess Championship in 2019. In 2001 Humpy won gold in the World junior Chess Championship. She also won gold British Women\'s Championship (2000, 2002) and came second in the FIDE Woman\'s Prix 2009-2011 and finished in overall second position. Since then, she has participated and won many major international and national chess championships. ', 'For her contribution to chess, she won the Arjuna Award and Padma Sri.', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide582.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(583, 'Sania Mirza', 'Sania Mirza is an Indian former international tennis player. She started playing tennis at the age of six and was coached by her father and Roger Anderson. She was a former world no.1 and also won six major titles. Mirza was a singles champion and beat many for world-number-ones, but she shifted to doubles after a serious wrist injury. Partnering with Martina Hingis, she won three major Grand Slams - Wimbledon, US Open, and the Australian Open. In mixed doubles, she has won 3 Grand Slams - Australian Open (Mahesh Bhupathi), French Open (Mahesh Bhupathi), and the US Open (Bruno Soares). Along with these, she has won many WTA, Asian Games, Commonwealth Games, and Afro Asian championships. \r\n', 'Mirza is the third Indian woman to win a match at a major, and the first to advance past the second round.', '', 'girl', '', 'sports, tennis', 'Slide583.PNG', 'proposed', 'tbd', NULL),
