(605, 'Homai Vyarawalla', 'Homai Vyarawalla was India\'s first female photojournalist. She was born into a Parsi Zoroastrian family in 1913. After she moved to Bombay, she studied at the prestigious Bombay University and Sir J.J. School of Art. When she first started her career, people thought she was just fooling around with the camera and did not bother much. This helped her capture natural and realistic photos in sensitive parts of the countrry with no one stopping her. She also captured many pictures of Gandhi, Jawaharlal Nehru, Muhammed Ali Jinnah and the Nehru-Gandhi family. Homai stopped her career in photography after the death of her husband stating that it was not worth it anymore. She died on 15th January, 2012 at Vadodara, India.', 'She is well known for having captured the 14th Dalai Lama\'s arrival in Sikkim, India for the first time via the Nathu La.', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide605.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
