(626, 'Chando Tomar  ', 'Chandro Tomar is an Indian sharpshooter from Johri village, Uttar Pradesh. She is the oldest sharpshooter in the world. She learned shooting by chance when she took her granddaughter to the Johri Rifle Club. At the range, Chandro took a pistol when her granddaughter could not load it and fired her first shot - which was a bullseye. This impressed the coach, Farooq Pathan and he trained her in shooting. Chandro\'s niece Seema Tomar and her granddaughter both credit her and Prakashi Tomar for encouraging them in their shooting career. She also won a gold medal at the Veteran Shooting Championship held in Chennai. Chandor succumbed to Covid-19 and died on 30 April, 2021. In her biopic, Saand Ki Aankh, Bhumi Pednekar is seen playing Chandro\'s role. ', 'She is also known as the Shooter Dadi (Shooter Grandma).', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide626.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1');
