(654, 'Gurmeet Monga ', 'Guneet Monga is an Indian film producer and CEO of Sikhya Entertainment. She was born in Delhi and recieved a degree in Mass Communications from MBICEM. She shifted to Mumbai in 2006 and started working on her first film, Say Salaam India. Guneet\'s first international award was the Student Academy Award - Narrative in 2009 for Kavi. Along with Anurag Kashyap, she has done many films such as Gangs of Wasseypur, That Girl in Yellow Boots, etc.', 'She has won two Academy Awards (Oscars) till now - the first for Period. End of Sentence in 2019, and The Elephant Whisperers in 2023.', '', 'girl', '', '', 'Slide654.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(655, 'Bhanu Athaiya', 'Bhanu Athaiya was an Indian costume designer and painter. She studied at Sir J J School of Art. There, she won the Usha Dehmukh Gold Medal  for one of her paintings. Soon after, she started working part-time as a freelance fashion illustrator for woman\'s magazines. Bhanu soon had a career change and started dessigning for Guru Datt\'s movies such as C.I.D, Pyaasa, Chaudvin ka Chand, etc. In 2012, she was diagnosed with a brain tumor and subsequently, she died on Oct 15, 2020 at the age of 91.', 'She was the first Indian to have recieved an Academy (Oscar) Award.', 'Movies', 'girl', '', 'oscar ', 'Slide655.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', 'book1'),
