(660, 'Rajani - Gayatri', 'Ranjani and Gayatri are sisters who perform as a Carnatic vocal and violin duo. They were born into a Tamil family and their mother was a vocalist as well. Ranjani was able to identify complex rythms at the tender age of five while Gayatri was able to identify over 100 ragams at the age of two . They started taking violin classes when they were young and can now perform in many Indian languages. As composers, they have set to music many bhajans. This sister duo has gave performances in foreign countries as well.', 'They are not only known for their singing but for their reverse combination Kanjivaram Sarees.', 'singers', 'girl', '', 'classical singers', 'Slide660.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
