(662, 'Jasu Shilpi', 'Jasu Shilpi was an Indian bronze sculptor. She made more than 525 bust and 225 large sized sculptures. She made figures of many famous personalities including Gandhiji, Subhash Chandra Bose, etc. Her works of Gandhiji and Martin Luther King Jr. have been installed in Florida University (Jacksonville), Chicago, and City of Charlotte, North Carolina. She died on 14 January, 2013 after suffering from a severe cardiac arrest. She was busy making a figure of Amitabh Bachchan that remained incomplete.', 'She is known as the \'Bronze Woman of India\'.', 'Profession', 'girl', '', 'Sculptor', 'Slide662.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'edit', 'book1'),
