(664, 'Dr. Madhuri Kanitkar', 'Dr. Madhuri Kanitkar is a decorated former General Officer in the Indian Army. She was born in Dharwad, Karnataka and joined the Armed Forces Medical College, Pune in 1978. She was awarded the President\'s Gold Medal for the best outgoing student of the graduate wing. She completed her post-graduation in 1990 and earned the Doctor of Medicine degree in pediatrics. Kanitkar then served the Indian Army as Major General Medical at the Northern Command, Udhampur. She was promoted to the post of Lieutenant General in 2020. She became only the third woman to have been holding this post. For her relentless work, she has been awarded with the Param Visisht Seva Medal, Ati Visisht Seva Medal, etc.', 'Kanitkar and her husband, Lieutenant General, Rajeev Kanitkar are the first couple in the Indian Armed Forces to achieve the three-star rank. ', 'Army', 'girl', '', 'profession', 'Slide664.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', 'book1'),
