(678, 'Dr. Lathika ath', 'Dr. Lathika Nath is an Indian author, photographer, and wildlife conservationist. She has been working since 1990 for the conservation of tigers. She spent most of her childhood travelling to places that had a lot of greenery and wilderness which established her life for nature and animals. Lathika graduated in environmental science from the University of Delhi. She also recieved her D.Phil at the WildCRU, Department of Zoology, Christ Church, Oxford. She has travelled a lot and has photographed many species and worked towards measures for their protection but later shifted her focus to solve human-wildlife conflicts. Lathika also has the merit of being the first person to have a PhD on tigers.', 'She is also known as \'The Tiger Princess\' and was also conferred with the title \'Her Daringness\'.', NULL, 'girl', NULL, 'aka first', 'Slide678.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
