(681, 'Sheila Sri Prakash (Architect)', 'Sheila Prakash is an Indian architect. She is the founder and CEO of Shilpa Architects and is also an Urban Designer. She learnt Bharatanatyam, Kuchipudi, painting, sculpting, and Classical music at a very young age and was known as a child prodigy. Sheila was selected for the renovation and preeservation of the Brihadisvara Temple in Thanjavur. She has worked on many big-scale projects. She was also featured as one of the female architects designing the future by Time Inc.', 'Sheila is the first woman of Indian origin to havestarted and operated her own architectural practice.', 'profession', 'girl', '', 'architect', 'Slide681.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', 'book1'),
(682, 'Sucheta Kripalani', 'Sucheta Kripalani was an Indian freedom fighter and politician. She was born in Ambala, Punjab and recieved her Master\'s in History from St.Stephen\'s College. She had exceptional courage in her from a young age and she could not tolerate Indians succumbing to the British. She came into the spotlight during the Quit India Movement and she later worked close with Mahatma Gandhi during the Partition row. She was active in politics even after independence in 1947. She died on December 1, 1974.', 'Sucheta Kripalani was the first Woman Chief Minister of India. She was elected the fourth chief minister of Uttar Pradesh and served a term of four years from 1963-1967.', 'politics', 'girl', 'UP', 'people politics', 'Slide682.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(683, 'Sudha Murthy', 'Sudha Murthy is an Indian philanthropist and author. She was born into a Kannada speaking family in Shiggaon. She completed a B.Eng in Electronic and Electronic Engineering from the B.V.B. College. Murty became the first female engineer employed by Tata (TELCO) when she wrote a letter to the company\'s chairman regarding the \'men only\' rule. Sudha Murty has authored many fictional and non-fictional books for children. She is also an active columnist in Kannada and English newspapers. ', 'Sudha Murthy married Infosys\' co-founder, Narayana Murthy, and her son-in-law Rishi Sunak was the prime minister of the UK at the time of writing.', 'people', 'girl', 'KA', 'literature writer philanthropist', 'Slide683.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', 'book1'),
(684, 'C B Muthamma', 'CB Muthamma was the first woman to clear the Indian Civil Services (ICS) exam. She was born in Coorg, Karnataka and when her father died, Muthamma\'s mother committed herself to educate her four children to the best of her capability. She completed her schooling n St. Josephs Girls School and got a Master of Arts degree in English Litereture from the Presidency College. She became the first female Indian ambassador when she was sent to Hungary in 1970. She was also a well-known philanthropist and donated her personal property to The Missionaries of Charity, a school for orphans.', 'She was also the first Indian woman diplomat.', NULL, 'girl', NULL, 'first', 'Slide684.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(685, 'Pratiba Patil', 'tbd', 'tbd', NULL, 'girl', NULL, NULL, 'Slide685.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', NULL),
(686, 'Bandaru Achchamamba', 'Bandaru Achchamamba was a pioneer in the early stages of the women\'s movement. She encouraged women to educate themsleves and created awareness by writing books. She is also regarded as one of the first feminist historians in India. She was born in Penganchprolu, Andhra Pradesh and was married to her maternal uncle, Bhandaru Madhava Rao. As he did not approve of Achchamamba continuing her education, she got her brother Komarraju venkata Lakshmana Rao to stay with them. She learned to read Telugu, Hindi, Marathi, and English by sitting next to him. Later, she learnt Bengali, Gujarati, and Sanskrit on her own. Dhana Trayodasi, Abala Sachcharita Ratnamala, and Khana are a few of her literary works.', 'Collaborating with Oruganti Sundari Ratanamba, Achchamamba founded the first women\'s association in Coastal Andhra - the Brindavana Streela Samajam.', 'literature', 'girl', 'AP', 'regional, people, literature', 'Slide686.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', 'book1'),
