(693, 'Lavanya Srinivas Gade', 'Lavanya Srinivas is an Indian storyteller, translator, professional trainer, and teacher. She was born and brought up in Madras. She comes from a very illustrious family surrounded by literary stalwarts. After getting married, she moved to Vishakhapatnam and taught English at the local Kendriya Vidyalaya. It was during this time that she realized children connected more with stories and discovered her passion for storytelling. Lavanya has founded Katha Kamamishu, a platform where she invites the public and weaves beautiful stories. She also participates in many storytelling sessions, mesmerizing both kids and adults. She serves on the editorial board of \"gaduggai,\" a web-based children\'s monthly publication. Lavanya depicts wonderful scenarios in a simple manner, and her voice modulation enhances the delight of the story. Her main goal is to make children aware of and proud of their Indian culture and traditions.', 'Her son Satwik Gade is an illustrator, political cartoonist, writer, and graphic designer. His work has been featured in The Hindu, First Post, BuzzFeed, and many other portals. He illustrates children\'s books for KaradiTales, Tulika Books, and BLPS.', 'people', 'girl', 'NA', '', 'Slide693.PNG', 'proposed', 'TBD: Balantrapu', 'book1'),
