(697, 'Saraswati Rajamani (spy)', 'Saraswathi Rajamani was an Indian spy and veteran of the Indian National Army (INA). She was born in Rangoon, Burma into an affluent and patriotic family. Her first direct interaction with Subhash Chandra Bose was when she donated all her jewellery to the INA and was adamant the he use it for the army. Once she joined the Rani of Jhansi regiment, she uncovered the plan of assasinating Bose and disguised as a boy, Mani, she used to carry the secrets of the Britishers to Netaji. Rajamani\'s bravery was proved when she risked her life, dressed up as a dancer, impressed the guards and released one of her colleagues who was in captivity. While she was escaping, she was shot in the leg but she still managed to reach safety.', 'Even after the Indian Independence Struggle, she still helped her country by contributing to Tsunami Funds and the Netaji Subhash Birthplace National Museum.', NULL, 'girl', NULL, NULL, 'Slide697.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(698, 'Durgawati Devi (spy)', 'Durgavati Devi was one of the few female Indian revolutionaries and freedom fighters who actively participated in armed revolution against the British. She was born in Allahabad and was married to Bhagwati Charan Vohra, who was also a patriot. Devi, along with her toddler son posed as Bhagat Singh\'s wife and son, and along with Sukhdev escaped to Kanpur after the killing of John P. Saunders. After Singh surrendered himself to the police, she tried to assassinate Lord Hailey, but was caught and imprisoned for three years. After India gained independence, she lived a simple life as a commoner and died in Ghaziabad at the age of 92.', 'Her husband was an active member of the Hindustan Socialist Republican Association and hence she was known as Durga Bhabhi among the other revolutionaries.', NULL, 'girl', NULL, NULL, 'Slide698.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(699, 'Noor Inayat Khan (spy)', 'Noor Inayat Khan was a British resistance agent in France who served in World War II. She served in the Special Operations Executive as an Allied spy who helped French prisoners escape from German territories. She joined the Women\'s Auxiliary Air Force and conduted wireless operations and morse code. Once when she was in German territory, she was betrayed by one of her colleagues and was captured by the enemy. Though she tried to escape, she was caught and tortured, yet she did not reveal any information about the Allied forces. This enraged the Germans and they executed her along with three of her teammates.', 'Noor\'s last word before dying was reported to be \"Liberté\".', NULL, 'girl', NULL, NULL, 'Slide699.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'tbd', 'book1'),
(700, 'Azizun Nisa (spy)', 'Azizun Nisa, a courtesan from Kanpur, played a vital role in India\'s First War of Independence in 1857, a chapter often overshadowed by better-known figures. Born in Lucknow, Azizun Nisa showcased her strategic prowess and became involved in the rebellion after her well-known love affair with Shamsuddin Sawar. She spied for the native rebels, passing on crucial information to aid their cause. Despite being marginalized and targeted by the British after the revolt, she remained resilient. Azizun Nisa\'s most notable contribution was during the Siege of Cawnpore, where she established her headquarters and fought alongside the soldiers. She exemplified the strength of courtesans who were not only connoisseurs of arts and literature but also financing and strategizing against the British. Azizun Nisa\'s fate remains uncertain, with some sources mentioning her trial but not confirming her execution.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'In the time is Azizun Nisa, the courtesans were referred to as ‘Tawaifs‘. Only privileged women could become \'Tawaifs\' after rigorous training in the classical music, dances, and instruments.', NULL, 'girl', NULL, NULL, 'Slide700.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'TBD', 'book1'),
(1001, 'Kuchipudi', 'Kuchipudi is a classical dance form that originated in Andhra Pradesh. It is known for its quick footwork, expressive eye movements, and dramatic characterization. Kuchipudi costumes are similar to those of Bharatanatyam costumes, it is made from a silk saree and has a pallu on top and pleated fan underneath. ', 'A unique feature of Kuchipudi is the Tarangam, in which the performer dances on the edges of a brass plate. ', 'dance, classical', 'girl', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'dance, classical, girls, women', 'Slide1001.PNG', 'Art Work Done', ' Ria ', NULL),
(1002, 'Bharatha Natyam', 'Bharatanatyam is a major classical dance form that originated in Tamil Nadu. The dancers wear sarees with embroidered designs stitched to form beautiful pleats that fan out when the dancer forms certain poses. There are two different common styles of Bharatanatyam dresses, a skirt style or a pyjama style. ', 'Bharatanatyam is believed to be a dance dedicated to fire as the movements of the body in this art form resemble those of fire.', 'dance, classical', 'girl', 'Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh', 'dance, classical, girls, women', 'Slide1002.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1003, 'Odissi', 'Odissi is a classical dance form that originated in the coastal state Orissa. The dress is made from a silk saree with traditional designs embroidered on it. The front part of the saree is worn with a pleated fan or a separate cloth to ensure flexibility of movements by the dancer.', 'Odissi is believed to be the oldest existing Indian dance form based on archaeological evidence.', 'Dances', 'girl', 'Orissa', 'Classical, Odissi', 'Slide1003.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1004, 'Kathak Dancer', 'Kathak is a traditional dance in India. Kathak dancers wear a special outfit but it is very similar to a ghagra choli or a anarkali. Depending on the type of dance the outfit may change.', 'Kathak dates back to the 4th Century B.C!', 'regional, dances', 'girl', 'North India', 'dances, dresses, kathak', 'Slide1004.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1005, 'Mohiniyattam', 'Mohiniyattam is the traditional dance form of Kerala performed exclusively by women. The costume is made out of the highly sought after Kerala Kasavu saree, a creamy white saree with rich golden borders. As many other Indian classical dance costumes, it also has a pleated fan that goes around the waist.', 'The attire for this dance form is very specific, only gold jewelry, jasmine flowers, and Kerala Kasavu sarees are used. ', 'dance, classical', 'girl', 'Kerala', 'dance, classical, girls, women', 'Slide1005.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1006, 'Cricketer (female)', 'The female cricketer uniform is very similar to the male cricketer uniform. It contains the full sleeves shirt and long pants. In addition, shin guards and sturdy running shoes. A cricket-style hat is also worn. During certain parts of the cricket game, a much sturdier helmet is worn. The Indian cricket color is blue, so the entire uniform is in that color. ', 'Some famous Indian female cricketers include Mithali Raj, Harmanpreet Kaur, and Jhulan Goswami.', 'Profession', 'girl', 'All', 'Cricket, Shin Guards, Hat, Helmet, Blue', 'Slide1006.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1007, 'Tennis Player (Female)', 'Tennis is a commonly played sport in India. Female players usually wear fitted tops and short skirts. Tennis was introduced to India in the 1880s under British colonial rule', 'Sania Mirza is one of the most popular Indian Female Tennis players', 'profession, sport', 'girl', 'all', 'tennis, racket, skirt', 'Slide1007.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1008, 'Navy Captain (Woman)', 'The Indian navy is part of the Indian Armed Forces. Navy officers have very important jobs, as they protect maritime borders. Women and men can be officers. The job of the captain is especially important because they oversee all others and are in charge of everything. The typical outfit is a white suit like dress. Although navy blue colors are also used. \r\n', 'The Indian navy dates back to when Indus Valley Civilization was there!\r\n', 'regional', 'girl', 'India (all over)', 'navy, dress', 'Slide1008.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1009, 'Police Uniform', 'In the Indian police officer uniform, both the pants and shirt are the color \'khaki\' which is an Indian word for dust, ashes, and earth. There is also a police peak cap with the Indian police insignia written on it. Officers are required to wear a badge, and sometimes other ranking pins and badges on their uniform. ', 'India has over 1 million police officers!', 'police', 'girl', 'ALL', 'khaki, uniform, officer, police, cap, pin, badge', 'Slide1009.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1010, 'Air Force Pilot (Woman)', 'The female Indian Air Force Pilots wear an outfit that is nearly identical to the males. The color is a bluish gray. Full pants and full sleeves shirt is generally is worn heavy duty shoes. A hat or helmet is also customary. Medals and honorary badges that individuals may have received are usually also displayed on the front of the shirt.', 'There are approximately 3,000 women in the Indian Air Force', 'profession', 'girl', 'All', 'Air force, pilot, medals', 'Slide1010.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1011, 'Lawyer (Female)', 'The dress code for lawyers in india is governed by the Bar Council of India Rules under the Advocates Act, 1961. They require every lawyer wear a black coat or robe with a white shirt and neckband. Females can also wear a white saree.', 'Anna Chandy (1905–1996), was the first female judge (1937) and then High Court judge (1959) in India. She was, in fact, one of the first female judges in the British Empire.', 'occupational', 'girl', 'All', 'lawyer, women, black, dress code', 'Slide1011.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1012, 'Chef (Female)', 'A traditional restaurant chef in India wears a white button down shirt with plain dark colored pants and sturdy shoes.', 'Maneet Chauhan, Nita Mehta, and Shipra Khanna are a few of the famous female Indian chefs.', 'proffesion', 'girl', 'All', 'chef, hat, food', 'Slide1012.PNG', 'Art Work Done', '', NULL),
(1013, 'Burrakatha Artist', 'Burra Katha, also spelled Burrakatha, is an oral storytelling technique in the Jangam Katha tradition, performed in villages of Andhra Pradesh. The troupe consists of one main performer and two co-performers. It is a narrative entertainment that consists of prayers, solo drama, dance, songs, poems, and jokes. The main storyteller (kathakudu) narrates the story. He plays tambura and dances to music. He also wears a metal ring called an andelu on his right thumb, holds another ring in his other hand, and adds more music by colliding with them frequently.', 'Burrakatha was the primary form of entertainment and awareness in the villages before widespread communication methods.', 'regional', 'boy', 'AP,  TN', '', 'Slide1013.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL),
(1014, 'Hari Katha Artist ', 'Harikatha is a form of Hindu storytelling in which the singer explores a traditional theme, often from the life of an Indian epic. The person telling the story through songs, music, and narration is called a Haridasa.', 'Usually, the narration involves numerous sub-plots and anecdotes, which are used to emphasize various aspects of the main story.', 'people', 'girl', 'TBD', '', 'Slide1014.PNG', 'Art Work Done', 'Bookmark', NULL);
